v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

39static inline bool IsZero(const Operand& rt) {
40 if (rt.is_reg()) {
41 return rt.rm() == zero_reg;
42 } else {
43 return rt.immediate() == 0;
44 }
45}
46
47int MacroAssembler::RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
48 Register exclusion1,
49 Register exclusion2,
50 Register exclusion3) const {
51 int bytes = 0;
52
53 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
54 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
55 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
56
57 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
58 bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
59 }
60
61 return bytes;
62}
63
64int MacroAssembler::PushCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion1,
65 Register exclusion2, Register exclusion3) {
66 int bytes = 0;
67
68 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
69 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
70 MultiPush(list);
71 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
72
73 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
74 MultiPushFPU(kCallerSavedFPU);
75 bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
76 }
77
78 return bytes;
79}
80
81int MacroAssembler::PopCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion1,
82 Register exclusion2, Register exclusion3) {
83 int bytes = 0;
84 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
85 MultiPopFPU(kCallerSavedFPU);
86 bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
87 }
88
89 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
90 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
91 MultiPop(list);
92 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
93
94 return bytes;
95}

97#define __ ACCESS_MASM(masm)
98namespace {
99#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
100// Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
101static void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
102 Register optimized_code_entry,
103 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
104 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
105 // -- a0 : actual argument count
106 // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
107 // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
108 // -----------------------------------
109 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
110 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code_entry, a1, a3, scratch1, scratch2));
111
112 Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
113
114 // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
115 // marker field.
116 __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
117 &heal_optimized_code_slot);
118
119 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
120 __ LoadCodePointerField(
121 optimized_code_entry,
122 FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
123
124 // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
125 // runtime to clear it.
126 __ JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
127 &heal_optimized_code_slot);
128
129 // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
130 // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
131 // The feedback vector is no longer used, so re-use it as a scratch
132 // register.
133 __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, a1);
134
135 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
136 __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, optimized_code_entry, kJSEntrypointTag);
137 __ Jump(a2);
138
139 // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
140 // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
141 // and re-enter the closure's code.
142 __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
143 __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
144}
145#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
146
147} // namespace

149void MacroAssembler::AssertFeedbackCell(Register object, Register scratch) {
150 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
151 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
152 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackCell, scratch,
153 Operand(FEEDBACK_CELL_TYPE));
154 }
155}
156void MacroAssembler::AssertFeedbackVector(Register object, Register scratch) {
157 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
158 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
159 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackVector, scratch,
160 Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
161 }
162}
163void MacroAssembler::AssertUnreachable(AbortReason reason) {
164 if (v8_flags.debug_code) Abort(reason);
165}
166#endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE

168void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
169 Register optimized_code, Register closure) {
170 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
171 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure));
172#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
173 UNREACHABLE();
174#else
175 StoreCodePointerField(optimized_code,
176 FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
177 RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, optimized_code,
178 kRAHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore, SmiCheck::kOmit,
179 SlotDescriptor::ForCodePointerSlot());
180#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
181}
182
183void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
184 Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
185 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
186 // -- a0 : actual argument count
187 // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee)
188 // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee)
189 // -----------------------------------
190 {
191 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
192 // Push a copy of the target function, the new target and the actual
193 // argument count.
194 // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
195 SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
196 Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
197 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
198
199 CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
200 // Use the return value before restoring a0
201 LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, a0, kJSEntrypointTag);
202 // Restore target function, new target and actual argument count.
203 Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
204 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
205 SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
206 }
207
208 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
209 Jump(a2);
210}
211
212Condition MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndCheckIfNeedsProcessing(
213 Register flags, Register feedback_vector, Register result,
214 CodeKind current_code_kind) {
215 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
216 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
217 DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
218
219 Lhu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
220 uint32_t kFlagsMask = FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested |
221 FeedbackVector::kFlagsMaybeHasTurbofanCode |
222 FeedbackVector::kFlagsLogNextExecution;
223 if (current_code_kind != CodeKind::MAGLEV) {
224 kFlagsMask |= FeedbackVector::kFlagsMaybeHasMaglevCode;
225 }
226 And(result, flags, Operand(kFlagsMask));
227 return ne;
228}
229
230// Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
231// is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
232void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
233 Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
234 Label* flags_need_processing) {
235 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
236 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
237 DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
238 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
239 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
240 Lhu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
241 uint32_t flag_mask =
242 FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
243 And(scratch, flags, Operand(flag_mask));
244 Branch(flags_need_processing, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
245}
246
247void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
248 Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
249 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
250 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
251#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
252 // In the leaptiering case, we don't load optimized code from the feedback
253 // vector so only need to call CompileOptimized or FunctionLogNextExecution
254 // here. See also LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing above.
255 Label needs_logging;
256 {
257 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
258 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
259 And(scratch, flags,
260 Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
261 Branch(&needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
262 }
263 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
264 bind(&needs_logging);
265 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
266#else
267 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
268 temps.Include(t0, t1);
269 Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
270 // Check if optimized code is available.
271 {
272 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
273 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
274 And(scratch, flags,
275 Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
276 Branch(&maybe_needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
277 Label::Distance::kNear);
278 }
279 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
280
281 bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
282 {
283 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
284 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
285 And(scratch, flags, Operand(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
286 Branch(&maybe_has_optimized_code, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
287 Label::Distance::kNear);
288 }
289
290 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
291
292 bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
293 Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
294 LoadTaggedField(optimized_code_entry,
295 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
296 FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
297 TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, temps.Acquire(),
298 temps.Acquire());
299#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
300}
301
302void MacroAssembler::LoadIsolateField(const Register& rd, IsolateFieldId id) {
303 li(rd, ExternalReference::Create(id));
304}
305
306void MacroAssembler::LoadRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
307#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
308 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
309 is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
310 DecompressTagged(destination, ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
311 return;
312 }
313#endif
314 // Many roots have addresses that are too large to fit into addition immediate
315 // operands. Evidence suggests that the extra instruction for decompression
316 // costs us more than the load.
317 LoadWord(destination,
318 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
319}
320
321void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
322 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
323 is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
324 li(destination, (int32_t)ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
325 return;
326 }
327 LoadWord(destination,
328 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
329}
330void MacroAssembler::LoadCompressedTaggedRoot(Register destination,
331 RootIndex index) {
332#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
333 Lwu(destination,
334 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
335#else
336 LoadWord(destination,
337 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
338#endif
339}

341void MacroAssembler::PushCommonFrame(Register marker_reg) {
342 if (marker_reg.is_valid()) {
343 Push(ra, fp, marker_reg);
344 AddWord(fp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
345 } else {
346 Push(ra, fp);
347 Mv(fp, sp);
348 }
349}
350
351void MacroAssembler::PushStandardFrame(Register function_reg) {
352 int offset = -StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset;
353 if (function_reg.is_valid()) {
354 Push(ra, fp, cp, function_reg, kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
355 offset += 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
356 } else {
357 Push(ra, fp, cp, kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
358 offset += kSystemPointerSize;
359 }
360 AddWord(fp, sp, Operand(offset));
361}

363int MacroAssembler::SafepointRegisterStackIndex(int reg_code) {
364 // The registers are pushed starting with the highest encoding,
365 // which means that lowest encodings are closest to the stack pointer.
366 return kSafepointRegisterStackIndexMap[reg_code];
367}

369// Clobbers object, dst, value, and ra, if (ra_status == kRAHasBeenSaved)
370// The register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
371// tag is shifted away.
372void MacroAssembler::RecordWriteField(Register object, int offset,
373 Register value, RAStatus ra_status,
374 SaveFPRegsMode save_fp,
375 SmiCheck smi_check, SlotDescriptor slot) {
376 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value));
377 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
378 // catch stores of Smis.
379 Label done;
380
381 // Skip the barrier if writing a smi.
382 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
383 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
384 }
385
386 // Although the object register is tagged, the offset is relative to the start
387 // of the object, so offset must be a multiple of kTaggedSize.
388 DCHECK(IsAligned(offset, kTaggedSize));
389
390 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
391 Label ok;
392 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
393 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
394 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, scratch));
395 AddWord(scratch, object, offset - kHeapObjectTag);
396 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(kTaggedSize - 1));
397 BranchShort(&ok, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
398 Abort(AbortReason::kUnalignedCellInWriteBarrier);
399 bind(&ok);
400 }
401
402 RecordWrite(object, Operand(offset - kHeapObjectTag), value, ra_status,
403 save_fp, SmiCheck::kOmit, slot);
404
405 bind(&done);
406}

409 MemOperand field_operand,
410 IndirectPointerTag tag) {

413#else
414 LoadTaggedField(destination, field_operand);
415#endif
416}

418void MacroAssembler::StoreTrustedPointerField(Register value,
419 MemOperand dst_field_operand) {
420#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
421 StoreIndirectPointerField(value, dst_field_operand);
422#else
423 StoreTaggedField(value, dst_field_operand);
424#endif
425}

427#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
428void MacroAssembler::ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(Register destination,
429 Register handle,
430 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
431 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
432 // The tag implies which pointer table to use.
433 if (tag == kUnknownIndirectPointerTag) {
434 // In this case we have to rely on the handle marking to determine which
435 // pointer table to use.
436 Label is_trusted_pointer_handle, done;
437 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, handle));
438 And(destination, handle, kCodePointerHandleMarker);
439 Branch(&is_trusted_pointer_handle, eq, destination, Operand(zero_reg));
440 ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
441 Branch(&done);
442 bind(&is_trusted_pointer_handle);
443 ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle,
444 kUnknownIndirectPointerTag);
445 bind(&done);
446 } else if (tag == kCodeIndirectPointerTag) {
447 ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
448 } else {
449 ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
450 }
451}
452
453void MacroAssembler::ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(Register destination,
454 Register handle,
455 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
456 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
457 DCHECK_NE(tag, kCodeIndirectPointerTag);
458 DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
459
460 Register table = destination;
461 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
462 LoadWord(table, MemOperand{kRootRegister,
463 IsolateData::trusted_pointer_table_offset()});
464 SrlWord(handle, handle, kTrustedPointerHandleShift);
465 CalcScaledAddress(destination, table, handle,
466 kTrustedPointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
467 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(destination, 0));
468 // The LSB is used as marking bit by the trusted pointer table, so here we
469 // have to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
470 // Untag the pointer and remove the marking bit in one operation.
471 Register tag_reg = handle;
472 li(tag_reg, Operand(~(tag | kTrustedPointerTableMarkBit)));
473 and_(destination, destination, tag_reg);
474}
475
476void MacroAssembler::ResolveCodePointerHandle(Register destination,
477 Register handle) {
478 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
479 DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
480
481 Register table = destination;
482 li(table, ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_address());
483 SrlWord(handle, handle, kCodePointerHandleShift);
484 CalcScaledAddress(destination, table, handle, kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
485 LoadWord(destination,
486 MemOperand(destination, kCodePointerTableEntryCodeObjectOffset));
487 // The LSB is used as marking bit by the code pointer table, so here we have
488 // to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
489 Or(destination, destination, Operand(kHeapObjectTag));
490}
491
492void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(Register destination,
493 MemOperand field_operand,
494 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
495 DCHECK_NE(tag, kInvalidEntrypointTag);
496 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
497 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
498 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
499 li(scratch, ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_address());
500 Lwu(destination, field_operand);
501 SrlWord(destination, destination, kCodePointerHandleShift);
502 SllWord(destination, destination, kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
503 AddWord(scratch, scratch, destination);
504 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
505 if (tag != 0) {
506 li(scratch, Operand(tag));
507 xor_(destination, destination, scratch);
508 }
509}
510#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
511
512void MacroAssembler::LoadExternalPointerField(Register destination,
513 MemOperand field_operand,
514 ExternalPointerTag tag,
515 Register isolate_root) {
516 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, isolate_root));
517 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
518#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
519 DCHECK_NE(tag, kExternalPointerNullTag);
520 DCHECK(!IsSharedExternalPointerType(tag));
521 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
522 Register external_table = temps.Acquire();
523 if (isolate_root == no_reg) {
524 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
525 isolate_root = kRootRegister;
526 }
527 LoadWord(external_table,
528 MemOperand(isolate_root,
529 IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
530 Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
531 Lwu(destination, field_operand);
532 srli(destination, destination, kExternalPointerIndexShift);
533 slli(destination, destination, kExternalPointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
534 AddWord(external_table, external_table, destination);
535 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(external_table, 0));
536 temps.Include(external_table);
537 external_table = no_reg;
538 And(destination, destination, Operand(~tag));
539#else
540 LoadWord(destination, field_operand);
541#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
542}

544#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
545void MacroAssembler::LoadIndirectPointerField(Register destination,
546 MemOperand field_operand,
547 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
548#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
549 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
550 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
551 Register handle = t6;
552 DCHECK_NE(handle, destination);
553 Lwu(handle, field_operand);
554
555 ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
556#else
557 UNREACHABLE();
558#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
559}

561void MacroAssembler::StoreIndirectPointerField(Register value,
562 MemOperand dst_field_operand,
563 Trapper&& trapper) {
564#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
565 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
566 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
567 Lw(scratch,
568 FieldMemOperand(value, ExposedTrustedObject::kSelfIndirectPointerOffset));
569 Sw(scratch, dst_field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
570#else
571 UNREACHABLE();
572#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
573}
574#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64

576void MacroAssembler::MaybeSaveRegisters(RegList registers) {
577 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
578 MultiPush(registers);
579}
580
581void MacroAssembler::MaybeRestoreRegisters(RegList registers) {
582 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
583 MultiPop(registers);
584}
585
586void MacroAssembler::CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(Register object, Operand offset,
587 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode) {
588 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
589 RegList registers = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
590 MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
591
592 Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
593 Register slot_address_parameter =
594 WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
595
596 MoveObjectAndSlot(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, object, offset);
597
598 CallBuiltin(Builtins::EphemeronKeyBarrier(fp_mode));
599 MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
600}
601
602void MacroAssembler::CallIndirectPointerBarrier(Register object, Operand offset,
603 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
604 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
605 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
606 RegList registers =
607 IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
608 MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
609
610 MoveObjectAndSlot(
611 IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(),
612 IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), object,
613 offset);
614 li(IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::IndirectPointerTagRegister(),
615 Operand(tag));
616
617 CallBuiltin(Builtins::IndirectPointerBarrier(fp_mode));
618 MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
619}

621void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(Register object,
622 Operand offset,
623 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
624 StubCallMode mode) {
625 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
626 RegList registers = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
627 MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
628
629 Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
630 Register slot_address_parameter =
631 WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
632
633 MoveObjectAndSlot(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, object, offset);
634
635 CallRecordWriteStub(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, fp_mode, mode);
636
637 MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
638}
639
640void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStub(Register object, Register slot_address,
641 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
642 StubCallMode mode) {
643 // Use CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters if the object and slot registers
644 // need to be caller saved.
645 DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(), object);
646 DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), slot_address);
647 if (mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
648 auto wasm_target =
649 static_cast<Address>(wasm::WasmCode::GetRecordWriteBuiltin(fp_mode));
650 Call(wasm_target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
651 } else {
652 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RecordWrite(fp_mode));
653 }
654}
655
656void MacroAssembler::MoveObjectAndSlot(Register dst_object, Register dst_slot,
657 Register object, Operand offset) {
658 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
659 DCHECK_NE(dst_object, dst_slot);
660 // If `offset` is a register, it cannot overlap with `object`.
661 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!offset.IsImmediate(), offset.rm() != object);
662
663 // If the slot register does not overlap with the object register, we can
664 // overwrite it.
665 if (dst_slot != object) {
666 AddWord(dst_slot, object, offset);
667 mv(dst_object, object);
668 return;
669 }
670
671 DCHECK_EQ(dst_slot, object);
672
673 // If the destination object register does not overlap with the offset
674 // register, we can overwrite it.
675 if (offset.IsImmediate() || (offset.rm() != dst_object)) {
676 mv(dst_object, dst_slot);
677 AddWord(dst_slot, dst_slot, offset);
678 return;
679 }
680
681 DCHECK_EQ(dst_object, offset.rm());
682
683 // We only have `dst_slot` and `dst_object` left as distinct registers so we
684 // have to swap them. We write this as a add+sub sequence to avoid using a
685 // scratch register.
686 AddWord(dst_slot, dst_slot, dst_object);
687 SubWord(dst_object, dst_slot, dst_object);
688}
689
690// Clobbers object, address, value, and ra, if (ra_status == kRAHasBeenSaved)
691// The register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
692// tag is shifted away.
693void MacroAssembler::RecordWrite(Register object, Operand offset,
694 Register value, RAStatus ra_status,
695 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, SmiCheck smi_check,
696 SlotDescriptor slot) {
697 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value));
698
699 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
700 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
701 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
702 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, temp));
703 AddWord(temp, object, offset);
704#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
705 if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
706 LoadIndirectPointerField(temp, MemOperand(temp, 0),
707 slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
708 } else {
709 DCHECK(slot.contains_direct_pointer());
710 LoadTaggedField(temp, MemOperand(temp, 0));
711 }
712#else
713 LoadTaggedField(temp, MemOperand(temp));
714#endif
715 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongAddressOrValuePassedToRecordWrite, temp,
716 Operand(value));
717 }
718
719 if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
720 return;
721 }
722
723 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
724 // catch stores of smis and stores into the young generation.
725 Label done;
726
727 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
728 DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
729 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
730 }
731
732 {
733 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
734 CheckPageFlag(value, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
735 eq, // In RISC-V, it uses cc for a comparison with 0, so if
736 // no bits are set, and cc is eq, it will branch to done
737 &done);
738
739 CheckPageFlag(object, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
740 eq, // In RISC-V, it uses cc for a comparison with 0, so if
741 // no bits are set, and cc is eq, it will branch to done
742 &done);
743 }
744 // Record the actual write.
745 if (ra_status == kRAHasNotBeenSaved) {
746 push(ra);
747 }
748 Register slot_address = WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
749 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address, value));
750 // TODO(cbruni): Turn offset into int.
751 if (slot.contains_direct_pointer()) {
752 DCHECK(offset.IsImmediate());
753 AddWord(slot_address, object, offset);
754 CallRecordWriteStub(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
755 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
756 } else {
757 DCHECK(slot.contains_indirect_pointer());
758 CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object, offset, fp_mode,
759 slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
760 }
761 if (ra_status == kRAHasNotBeenSaved) {
762 pop(ra);
763 }
764 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) li(slot_address, Operand(kZapValue));
765
766 bind(&done);
767}
768
769// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
770// Instruction macros.
771#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
772void MacroAssembler::DecodeSandboxedPointer(Register value) {
773 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
774#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
775 srli(value, value, kSandboxedPointerShift);
776 AddWord(value, value, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
777#else
778 UNREACHABLE();
779#endif
780}
781
782void MacroAssembler::LoadSandboxedPointerField(
783 Register destination, const MemOperand& field_operand) {
784#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
785 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
786 LoadWord(destination, field_operand);
787 DecodeSandboxedPointer(destination);
788#else
789 UNREACHABLE();
790#endif
791}
792
793void MacroAssembler::StoreSandboxedPointerField(
794 Register value, const MemOperand& dst_field_operand) {
795#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
796 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
797 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
798 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
799 SubWord(scratch, value, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
800 slli(scratch, scratch, kSandboxedPointerShift);
801 StoreWord(scratch, dst_field_operand);
802#else
803 UNREACHABLE();
804#endif
805}
806
807void MacroAssembler::Add32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
808 if (rt.is_reg()) {
809 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
810 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
811 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
812 c_addw(rd, rt.rm());
813 } else {
814 addw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
815 }
816 } else {
817 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
818 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) &&
819 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
820 c_addiw(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
821 } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
822 addiw(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
823 } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
824 (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
825 addiw(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
826 addiw(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
827 } else {
828 // li handles the relocation.
829 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
830 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
831 Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
832 addw(rd, rs, scratch);
833 }
834 }
835}
836
837void MacroAssembler::Sub32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
838 if (rt.is_reg()) {
839 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
840 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
841 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
842 c_subw(rd, rt.rm());
843 } else {
844 subw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
845 }
846 } else {
847 DCHECK(is_int32(rt.immediate()));
848 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
849 (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
850 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
851 c_addiw(
852 rd,
853 static_cast<int8_t>(
854 -rt.immediate())); // No c_subiw instr, use c_addiw(x, y, -imm).
855 } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
856 addiw(rd, rs,
857 static_cast<int32_t>(
858 -rt.immediate())); // No subiw instr, use addiw(x, y, -imm).
859 } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
860 (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
861 addiw(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
862 addiw(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
863 } else {
864 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
865 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
866 if (-rt.immediate() >> 12 == 0 && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
867 // Use load -imm and addu when loading -imm generates one instruction.
868 Li(scratch, -rt.immediate());
869 addw(rd, rs, scratch);
870 } else {
871 // li handles the relocation.
872 Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
873 subw(rd, rs, scratch);
874 }
875 }
876 }
877}
878
879void MacroAssembler::AddWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
880 Add64(rd, rs, rt);
881}
882
883void MacroAssembler::SubWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
884 Sub64(rd, rs, rt);
885}
886
887void MacroAssembler::Sub64(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
888 if (rt.is_reg()) {
889 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
890 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
891 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
892 c_sub(rd, rt.rm());
893 } else {
894 sub(rd, rs, rt.rm());
895 }
896 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
897 (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
898 (rt.immediate() != 0) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
899 c_addi(rd,
900 static_cast<int8_t>(
901 -rt.immediate())); // No c_subi instr, use c_addi(x, y, -imm).
902
903 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(-rt.immediate()) &&
904 (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
905 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
906 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
907 c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(-rt.immediate()));
908 } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
909 addi(rd, rs,
910 static_cast<int32_t>(
911 -rt.immediate())); // No subi instr, use addi(x, y, -imm).
912 } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
913 (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
914 addi(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
915 addi(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
916 } else {
917 int li_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(rt.immediate());
918 int li_neg_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(-rt.immediate());
919 if (li_neg_count < li_count && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
920 // Use load -imm and add when loading -imm generates one instruction.
921 DCHECK(rt.immediate() != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
922 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
923 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
924 li(scratch, Operand(-rt.immediate()));
925 add(rd, rs, scratch);
926 } else {
927 // li handles the relocation.
928 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
929 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
930 li(scratch, rt);
931 sub(rd, rs, scratch);
932 }
933 }
934}
935
936void MacroAssembler::Add64(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
937 if (rt.is_reg()) {
938 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
939 (rt.rm() != zero_reg) && (rs != zero_reg)) {
940 c_add(rd, rt.rm());
941 } else {
942 add(rd, rs, rt.rm());
943 }
944 } else {
945 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
946 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
947 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
948 c_addi(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
949 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(rt.immediate()) &&
950 (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
951 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
952 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
953 c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(rt.immediate()));
954 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension &&
955 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) && (rs == sp) &&
956 is_uint10(rt.immediate()) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
957 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
958 c_addi4spn(rd, static_cast<uint16_t>(rt.immediate()));
959 } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
960 addi(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
961 } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
962 (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
963 addi(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
964 addi(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
965 } else {
966 // li handles the relocation.
967 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
968 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
969 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
970 li(scratch, rt);
971 add(rd, rs, scratch);
972 }
973 }
974}

1001void MacroAssembler::Mulhu32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
1002 Register rsz, Register rtz) {
1003 slli(rsz, rs, 32);
1004 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1005 slli(rtz, rt.rm(), 32);
1006 } else {
1007 Li(rtz, rt.immediate() << 32);
1008 }
1009 mulhu(rd, rsz, rtz);
1010 srai(rd, rd, 32);
1011}

1154 } else {
1155 add(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1156 }

1159 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
1160 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1161 c_addi(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
1162 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(rt.immediate()) &&
1163 (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
1164 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
1165 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {

1167 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension &&
1168 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) && (rs == sp) &&
1169 is_uint10(rt.immediate()) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
1170 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {

1172 } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1173 addi(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
1174 } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
1175 (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
1176 addi(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
1177 addi(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
1178 } else {

1192
1193void MacroAssembler::Sub32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1194 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1195 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1196 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
1197 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
1198 c_sub(rd, rt.rm());
1199 } else {
1200 sub(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1201 }
1202 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1203 (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
1204 (rt.immediate() != 0) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1205 c_addi(rd,
1206 static_cast<int8_t>(
1207 -rt.immediate())); // No c_subi instr, use c_addi(x, y, -imm).
1208
1209 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(-rt.immediate()) &&
1210 (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
1211 (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
1212 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1213 c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(-rt.immediate()));
1214 } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1215 addi(rd, rs,
1216 static_cast<int32_t>(
1217 -rt.immediate())); // No subi instr, use addi(x, y, -imm).
1218 } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
1219 (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
1220 addi(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
1221 addi(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
1222 } else {
1223 // RV32G todo: imm64 or imm32 here
1224 int li_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(rt.immediate());
1225 int li_neg_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(-rt.immediate());
1226 if (li_neg_count < li_count && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1227 // Use load -imm and add when loading -imm generates one instruction.
1228 DCHECK(rt.immediate() != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
1229 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1230 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1231 li(scratch, Operand(-rt.immediate()));
1232 add(rd, rs, scratch);
1233 } else {
1234 // li handles the relocation.
1235 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1236 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1237 li(scratch, rt);
1238 sub(rd, rs, scratch);
1239 }
1240 }
1241}

1245}

1334void MacroAssembler::And(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1335 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1336 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1337 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
1338 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
1339 c_and(rd, rt.rm());
1340 } else {
1341 and_(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1342 }
1343 } else {
1344 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
1345 !MustUseReg(rt.rmode()) && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1346 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
1347 c_andi(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
1348 } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1349 andi(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
1350 } else {
1351 // li handles the relocation.
1352 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1353 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1354 Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
1355 and_(rd, rs, scratch);
1356 }
1357 }
1358}
1359
1360void MacroAssembler::Or(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1361 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1362 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1363 ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
1364 ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
1365 c_or(rd, rt.rm());
1366 } else {
1367 or_(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1368 }
1369 } else {
1370 if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1371 ori(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
1372 } else {
1373 // li handles the relocation.
1374 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1375 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1376 Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
1377 or_(rd, rs, scratch);
1378 }
1379 }

1635void MacroAssembler::Ror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1636 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1637 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1638 rorw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1639 } else {
1640 int64_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1641 if (ror_value < 0) {
1642 ror_value += 32;
1643 }
1644 roriw(rd, rs, ror_value);
1645 }
1646 return;
1647 }
1648 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1649 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1650 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1651 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1652 negw(scratch, rt.rm());
1653 sllw(scratch, rs, scratch);
1654 srlw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1655 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1656 sext_w(rd, rd);
1657 } else {
1658 int64_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1659 if (ror_value == 0) {
1660 Mv(rd, rs);
1661 return;
1662 } else if (ror_value < 0) {
1663 ror_value += 32;
1664 }
1665 srliw(scratch, rs, ror_value);
1666 slliw(rd, rs, 32 - ror_value);
1667 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1668 sext_w(rd, rd);
1669 }
1670}
1671
1672void MacroAssembler::Dror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1673 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1674 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1675 ror(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1676 } else {
1677 int64_t dror_value = rt.immediate() % 64;
1678 if (dror_value < 0) {
1679 dror_value += 64;
1680 }
1681 rori(rd, rs, dror_value);
1682 }
1683 return;
1684 }
1685 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1686 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1687 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1688 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1689 negw(scratch, rt.rm());
1690 sll(scratch, rs, scratch);
1691 srl(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1692 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1693 } else {
1694 int64_t dror_value = rt.immediate() % 64;
1695 if (dror_value == 0) {
1696 Mv(rd, rs);
1697 return;
1698 } else if (dror_value < 0) {
1699 dror_value += 64;
1700 }
1701 srli(scratch, rs, dror_value);
1702 slli(rd, rs, 64 - dror_value);
1703 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1704 }
1705}

1746void MacroAssembler::Ror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1747 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1748 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1749 ror(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1750 } else {
1751 int32_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1752 if (ror_value < 0) {
1753 ror_value += 32;
1754 }
1755 rori(rd, rs, ror_value);
1756 }
1757 return;
1758 }
1759 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1760 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1761 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1762 if (rt.is_reg()) {
1763 neg(scratch, rt.rm());
1764 sll(scratch, rs, scratch);
1765 srl(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1766 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1767 } else {
1768 int32_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1769 if (ror_value == 0) {
1770 Mv(rd, rs);
1771 return;
1772 } else if (ror_value < 0) {
1773 ror_value += 32;
1774 }
1775 srli(scratch, rs, ror_value);
1776 slli(rd, rs, 32 - ror_value);
1777 or_(rd, scratch, rd);
1778 }
1779}

1782void MacroAssembler::Li(Register rd, intptr_t imm) {
1783 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(imm)) {
1784 c_li(rd, imm);
1785 } else {
1786 RV_li(rd, imm);
1787 }
1788}
1789
1790void MacroAssembler::Mv(Register rd, const Operand& rt) {
1791 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd != zero_reg) && (rt.rm() != zero_reg)) {
1792 c_mv(rd, rt.rm());
1793 } else {
1794 mv(rd, rt.rm());
1795 }
1796}
1797
1798void MacroAssembler::CalcScaledAddress(Register rd, Register rt, Register rs,
1799 uint8_t sa) {
1800 DCHECK(sa >= 1 && sa <= 31);
1801 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBA)) {
1802 switch (sa) {
1803 case 1:
1804 sh1add(rd, rs, rt);
1805 return;
1806 case 2:
1807 sh2add(rd, rs, rt);
1808 return;
1809 case 3:
1810 sh3add(rd, rs, rt);
1811 return;
1812 default:
1813 break;
1814 }
1815 }
1816 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1817 Register tmp = rd == rt ? temps.Acquire() : rd;
1818 DCHECK(tmp != rt);
1819 slli(tmp, rs, sa);
1820 AddWord(rd, rt, tmp);
1821 return;
1822}
1823
1824// ------------Pseudo-instructions-------------
1825// Change endianness
1826
1827template <int NBYTES>
1828void MacroAssembler::ReverseBytesHelper(Register rd, Register rs, Register tmp1,
1829 Register tmp2) {
1830 DCHECK(tmp1 != tmp2);
1831 DCHECK((rs != tmp1) && (rs != tmp2));
1832 DCHECK((rd != tmp1) && (rd != tmp2));
1833
1834 // ByteMask - maximum value, held in byte
1835 constexpr int ByteMask = (1 << kBitsPerByte) - 1;
1836 // tmp1 = rs[0]; take least byte
1837 // tmp1 = tmp1 << kBitsPerByte;
1838 // for (nbyte = 1; nbyte < NBYTES - 1; nbyte++) {
1839 // tmp2 = rs[nbyte]; take n`th byte
1840 // tmp1 = (tmp2 | tmp1) << kBitsPerByte; add n`th source byte to tmp1
1841 // }
1842 // rd[0] = rs[NBYTES-1]; take upper byte
1843 // rd[NBYTES-1 : 1] = tmp1[NBYTES-1 : 1]; fill other bytes
1844 andi(tmp1, rs, ByteMask);
1845 slli(tmp1, tmp1, kBitsPerByte);
1846 for (int nbyte = 1; nbyte < NBYTES - 1; nbyte++) {
1847 srli(tmp2, rs, nbyte * kBitsPerByte);
1848 andi(tmp2, tmp2, ByteMask);
1849 or_(tmp1, tmp1, tmp2);
1850 slli(tmp1, tmp1, kBitsPerByte);
1851 }
1852 srli(rd, rs, (NBYTES - 1) * kBitsPerByte);
1853 andi(rd, rd, ByteMask);
1854 or_(rd, tmp1, rd);
1855}
1856
1857#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
1858void MacroAssembler::ByteSwap(Register rd, Register rs, int operand_size,
1859 Register scratch) {
1860 DCHECK(operand_size == 4 || operand_size == 8);
1861 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1862 rev8(rd, rs);
1863 if (operand_size == 4) {
1864 srai(rd, rd, 32);
1865 }
1866 return;
1867 }
1868 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
1869 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
1870 if (operand_size == 4) {
1871 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1872 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1873 DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1874 Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1875 Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1876 if (scratch == no_reg) {
1877 ReverseBytesHelper<8>(rd, rs, x0, x1);
1878 srai(rd, rd, 32);
1879 } else {
1880 // Uint32_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF;
1881 // x0 = (x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16);
1882 // x0 = (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8));
1883 Register x2 = scratch;
1884 li(x1, 0x00FF00FF);
1885 slliw(x0, rs, 16);
1886 srliw(rd, rs, 16);
1887 or_(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16
1888 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF
1889 slliw(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1890 slliw(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00
1891 and_(rd, x0, x1); // x0 & 0xFF00FF00
1892 srliw(rd, rd, 8);
1893 or_(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1894 }
1895 } else {
1896 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1897 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1898 DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1899 Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1900 Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1901 if (scratch == no_reg) {
1902 ReverseBytesHelper<8>(rd, rs, x0, x1);
1903 } else {
1904 // uinx24_t x1 = 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFl;
1905 // uinx24_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFl;
1906 // x0 = (x0 << 32 | x0 >> 32);
1907 // x0 = (x0 & x1) << 16 | (x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16;
1908 // x0 = (x0 & x1) << 8 | (x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8;
1909 Register x2 = scratch;
1910 li(x1, 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFl);
1911 slli(x0, rs, 32);
1912 srli(rd, rs, 32);
1913 or_(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 32 | x0 >> 32
1914 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF
1915 slli(x2, x2, 16); // x2 <- (x0 & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF) << 16
1916 slli(x1, x1, 16); // x1 <- 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000
1917 and_(rd, x0, x1); // rd <- x0 & 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000
1918 srli(rd, rd, 16); // rd <- x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16
1919 or_(x0, rd, x2); // (x0 & x1) << 16 | (x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16;
1920 li(x1, 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFl);
1921 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF
1922 slli(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1923 slli(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00FF00FF00
1924 and_(rd, x0, x1);
1925 srli(rd, rd, 8); // rd <- (x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8
1926 or_(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1927 }
1928 }
1929}
1930
1931#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
1932void MacroAssembler::ByteSwap(Register rd, Register rs, int operand_size,
1933 Register scratch) {
1934 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1935 rev8(rd, rs);
1936 return;
1937 }
1938 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
1939 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
1940 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1941 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1942 DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1943 Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1944 Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1945 if (scratch == no_reg) {
1946 ReverseBytesHelper<4>(rd, rs, x0, x1);
1947 } else {
1948 // Uint32_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF;
1949 // x0 = (x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16);
1950 // x0 = (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8));
1951 Register x2 = scratch;
1952 li(x1, 0x00FF00FF);
1953 slli(x0, rs, 16);
1954 srli(rd, rs, 16);
1955 or_(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16
1956 and_(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF
1957 slli(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1958 slli(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00
1959 and_(rd, x0, x1); // x0 & 0xFF00FF00
1960 srli(rd, rd, 8);
1961 or_(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1962 }
1963}
1964#endif
1965
1966template <int NBYTES, bool LOAD_SIGNED>
1967void MacroAssembler::LoadNBytes(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs,
1968 Register scratch) {
1969 DCHECK(rd != rs.rm() && rd != scratch);
1970 DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
1971
1972 // load the most significant byte
1973 if (LOAD_SIGNED) {
1974 lb(rd, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1975 } else {
1976 lbu(rd, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1977 }
1978
1979 // load remaining (nbytes-1) bytes from higher to lower
1980 slli(rd, rd, 8 * (NBYTES - 1));
1981 for (int i = (NBYTES - 2); i >= 0; i--) {
1982 lbu(scratch, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + i);
1983 if (i) slli(scratch, scratch, i * 8);
1984 or_(rd, rd, scratch);
1985 }
1986}
1987
1988template <int NBYTES, bool LOAD_SIGNED>
1989void MacroAssembler::LoadNBytesOverwritingBaseReg(const MemOperand& rs,
1990 Register scratch0,
1991 Register scratch1) {
1992 // This function loads nbytes from memory specified by rs and into rs.rm()
1993 DCHECK(rs.rm() != scratch0 && rs.rm() != scratch1 && scratch0 != scratch1);
1994 DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
1995
1996 // load the most significant byte
1997 if (LOAD_SIGNED) {
1998 lb(scratch0, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
1999 } else {
2000 lbu(scratch0, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
2001 }
2002
2003 // load remaining (nbytes-1) bytes from higher to lower
2004 slli(scratch0, scratch0, 8 * (NBYTES - 1));
2005 for (int i = (NBYTES - 2); i >= 0; i--) {
2006 lbu(scratch1, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + i);
2007 if (i) {
2008 slli(scratch1, scratch1, i * 8);
2009 or_(scratch0, scratch0, scratch1);
2010 } else {
2011 // write to rs.rm() when processing the last byte
2012 or_(rs.rm(), scratch0, scratch1);
2013 }
2014 }
2015}
2016
2017template <int NBYTES, bool IS_SIGNED>
2018void MacroAssembler::UnalignedLoadHelper(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2019 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2020 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2021
2022 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2023 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2024 MemOperand source = rs;
2025 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2026 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
2027 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2028 NBYTES - 1);
2029
2030 // Since source.rm() is scratch_base, assume rd != source.rm()
2031 DCHECK(rd != source.rm());
2032 Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2033 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rd, source, scratch_other);
2034 } else {
2035 // no need to adjust base-and-offset
2036 if (rd != rs.rm()) {
2037 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2038 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rd, rs, scratch);
2039 } else { // rd == rs.rm()
2040 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2041 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
2042 LoadNBytesOverwritingBaseReg<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rs, scratch, scratch2);
2043 }
2044 }
2045}
2046
2047#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2048template <int NBYTES>
2049void MacroAssembler::UnalignedFLoadHelper(FPURegister frd,
2050 const MemOperand& rs) {
2051 DCHECK(NBYTES == 4 || NBYTES == 8);
2052 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2053 MemOperand source = rs;
2054 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2055 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2056 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2057 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2058 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
2059 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2060 NBYTES - 1);
2061 }
2062 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2063 Register scratch_other = no_reg;
2064 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
2065 scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2066 } else {
2067 push(t2);
2068 scratch_other = t2;
2069 }
2070 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
2071 scratch_other != rs.rm());
2072 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
2073 if (NBYTES == 4)
2074 fmv_w_x(frd, scratch);
2075 else
2076 fmv_d_x(frd, scratch);
2077 if (scratch_other == t2) {
2078 pop(t2);
2079 }
2080}
2081#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2082template <int NBYTES>
2083void MacroAssembler::UnalignedFLoadHelper(FPURegister frd,
2084 const MemOperand& rs) {
2085 DCHECK_EQ(NBYTES, 4);
2086 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2087 MemOperand source = rs;
2088 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2089 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2090 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2091 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2092 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
2093 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2094 NBYTES - 1);
2095 }
2096 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2097 Register scratch_other = no_reg;
2098 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
2099 scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2100 } else {
2101 push(t2);
2102 scratch_other = t2;
2103 }
2104 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
2105 scratch_other != rs.rm());
2106 LoadNBytes<NBYTES, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
2107 fmv_w_x(frd, scratch);
2108 if (scratch_other == t2) {
2109 pop(t2);
2110 }
2111}
2112
2113void MacroAssembler::UnalignedDoubleHelper(FPURegister frd,
2114 const MemOperand& rs) {
2115 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2116 MemOperand source = rs;
2117 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2118 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2119 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, 8 - 1)) {
2120 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2121 DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
2122 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2123 8 - 1);
2124 }
2125 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2126 Register scratch_other = no_reg;
2127 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
2128 scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2129 } else {
2130 push(t2);
2131 scratch_other = t2;
2132 }
2133 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
2134 scratch_other != rs.rm());
2135 LoadNBytes<4, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
2136 SubWord(sp, sp, 8);
2137 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2138 source.set_offset(source.offset() + 4);
2139 LoadNBytes<4, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
2140 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
2141 LoadDouble(frd, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2142 AddWord(sp, sp, 8);
2143 if (scratch_other == t2) {
2144 pop(t2);
2145 }
2146}
2147#endif
2148
2149template <int NBYTES>
2150void MacroAssembler::UnalignedStoreHelper(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs,
2151 Register scratch_other) {
2152 DCHECK(scratch_other != rs.rm());
2153 DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
2154 MemOperand source = rs;
2155 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2156 Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2157 // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2158 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2159 DCHECK(scratch_base != rd && scratch_base != rs.rm());
2160 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2161 NBYTES - 1);
2162 }
2163
2164 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2165 if (scratch_other == no_reg) {
2166 if (temps.CanAcquire()) {
2167 scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2168 } else {
2169 push(t2);
2170 scratch_other = t2;
2171 }
2172 }
2173
2174 DCHECK(scratch_other != rd && scratch_other != rs.rm() &&
2175 scratch_other != source.rm());
2176
2177 sb(rd, source.rm(), source.offset());
2178 for (size_t i = 1; i <= (NBYTES - 1); i++) {
2179 srli(scratch_other, rd, i * 8);
2180 sb(scratch_other, source.rm(), source.offset() + i);
2181 }
2182 if (scratch_other == t2) {
2183 pop(t2);
2184 }
2185}
2186
2187#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2188template <int NBYTES>
2189void MacroAssembler::UnalignedFStoreHelper(FPURegister frd,
2190 const MemOperand& rs) {
2191 DCHECK(NBYTES == 8 || NBYTES == 4);
2192 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2193 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2194 if (NBYTES == 4) {
2195 fmv_x_w(scratch, frd);
2196 } else {
2197 fmv_x_d(scratch, frd);
2198 }
2199 UnalignedStoreHelper<NBYTES>(scratch, rs);
2200}
2201#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2202template <int NBYTES>
2203void MacroAssembler::UnalignedFStoreHelper(FPURegister frd,
2204 const MemOperand& rs) {
2205 DCHECK_EQ(NBYTES, 4);
2206 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2207 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2208 fmv_x_w(scratch, frd);
2209 UnalignedStoreHelper<NBYTES>(scratch, rs);
2210}
2211void MacroAssembler::UnalignedDStoreHelper(FPURegister frd,
2212 const MemOperand& rs) {
2213 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2214 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2215 Sub32(sp, sp, 8);
2216 StoreDouble(frd, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2217 Lw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2218 UnalignedStoreHelper<4>(scratch, rs);
2219 Lw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
2220 MemOperand source = rs;
2221 source.set_offset(source.offset() + 4);
2222 UnalignedStoreHelper<4>(scratch, source);
2223 Add32(sp, sp, 8);
2224}
2225#endif

2227template <typename Reg_T, typename Func>
2228void MacroAssembler::AlignedLoadHelper(Reg_T target, const MemOperand& rs,
2229 Func generator) {
2230 MemOperand source = rs;
2231 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2232 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2233 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(source)) {
2234 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2235 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm());
2236 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch);
2237 }
2238 generator(target, source);
2239}
2240
2241template <typename Reg_T, typename Func>
2242void MacroAssembler::AlignedStoreHelper(Reg_T value, const MemOperand& rs,
2243 Func generator) {
2244 MemOperand source = rs;
2245 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2246 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2247 if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(source)) {
2248 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2249 // make sure scratch does not overwrite value
2250 if (std::is_same<Reg_T, Register>::value)
2251 DCHECK(scratch.code() != value.code());
2252 DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm());
2253 AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch);
2254 }
2255 generator(value, source);
2256}

2286#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2287// Load consequent 32-bit word pair in 64-bit reg. and put first word in low
2288// bits,
2289// second word in high bits.
2290void MacroAssembler::LoadWordPair(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2291 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2292 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2293 Lwu(rd, rs);
2294 Lw(scratch, MemOperand(rs.rm(), rs.offset() + kSystemPointerSize / 2));
2295 slli(scratch, scratch, 32);
2296 AddWord(rd, rd, scratch);
2297}
2298
2299// Do 64-bit store as two consequent 32-bit stores to unaligned address.
2300void MacroAssembler::StoreWordPair(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2301 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2302 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2303 Sw(rd, rs);
2304 srai(scratch, rd, 32);
2305 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(rs.rm(), rs.offset() + kSystemPointerSize / 2));
2306}
2307#endif

2385void MacroAssembler::Lw(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {
2386 auto fn = [&](Register target, const MemOperand& source) {
2387 trapper(pc_offset());
2388 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((target.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2389 ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2390 is_uint7(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x3) == 0)) {
2391 c_lw(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2392 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (target != zero_reg) &&
2393 is_uint8(source.offset()) && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2394 ((source.offset() & 0x3) == 0)) {
2395 c_lwsp(target, source.offset());
2396 } else {
2397 lw(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2398 }
2399 };
2400 AlignedLoadHelper(rd, rs, fn);
2401}

2412
2413void MacroAssembler::Sw(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {
2414 auto fn = [&](Register value, const MemOperand& source) {
2415 trapper(pc_offset());
2416 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((value.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2417 ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2418 is_uint7(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x3) == 0)) {
2419 c_sw(value, source.rm(), source.offset());
2420 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2421 is_uint8(source.offset()) && (((source.offset() & 0x3) == 0))) {
2422 c_swsp(value, source.offset());
2423 } else {
2424 sw(value, source.rm(), source.offset());
2425 }
2426 };
2427 AlignedStoreHelper(rd, rs, fn);
2428}
2429
2430#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2431void MacroAssembler::Ld(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {
2432 auto fn = [&](Register target, const MemOperand& source) {
2433 trapper(pc_offset());
2434 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((target.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2435 ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2436 is_uint8(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2437 c_ld(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2438 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (target != zero_reg) &&
2439 is_uint9(source.offset()) && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2440 ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2441 c_ldsp(target, source.offset());
2442 } else {
2443 ld(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2444 }
2445 };
2446 AlignedLoadHelper(rd, rs, fn);
2447}
2448
2449void MacroAssembler::Sd(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {
2450 auto fn = [&](Register value, const MemOperand& source) {
2451 trapper(pc_offset());
2452 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((value.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2453 ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2454 is_uint8(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2455 c_sd(value, source.rm(), source.offset());
2456 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2457 is_uint9(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2458 c_sdsp(value, source.offset());
2459 } else {
2460 sd(value, source.rm(), source.offset());
2461 }
2462 };
2463 AlignedStoreHelper(rd, rs, fn);
2464}
2465#endif

2468 Trapper&& trapper) {
2469 auto fn = [&](FPURegister target, const MemOperand& source) {
2470 trapper(pc_offset());
2471 flw(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2472 };

2474}

2485void MacroAssembler::LoadDouble(FPURegister fd, const MemOperand& src,
2486 Trapper&& trapper) {
2487 auto fn = [&](FPURegister target, const MemOperand& source) {
2488 trapper(pc_offset());
2489 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((target.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2490 ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2491 is_uint8(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2492 c_fld(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2493 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2494 is_uint9(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2495 c_fldsp(target, source.offset());
2496 } else {
2497 fld(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2498 }
2499 };
2500 AlignedLoadHelper(fd, src, fn);
2501}
2502
2503void MacroAssembler::StoreDouble(FPURegister fs, const MemOperand& src,
2504 Trapper&& trapper) {
2505 auto fn = [&](FPURegister value, const MemOperand& source) {
2506 trapper(pc_offset());
2507 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((value.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2508 ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2509 is_uint8(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2510 c_fsd(value, source.rm(), source.offset());
2511 } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2512 is_uint9(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x7) == 0)) {
2513 c_fsdsp(value, source.offset());
2514 } else {
2515 fsd(value, source.rm(), source.offset());
2516 }
2517 };
2518 AlignedStoreHelper(fs, src, fn);

2520
2521void MacroAssembler::Ll(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {
2522 bool is_one_instruction = rs.offset() == 0;
2523 if (is_one_instruction) {
2524 trapper(pc_offset());
2525 lr_w(false, false, rd, rs.rm());
2526 } else {
2527 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2528 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2529 AddWord(scratch, rs.rm(), rs.offset());
2530 trapper(pc_offset());
2531 lr_w(false, false, rd, scratch);
2532 }
2533}
