2580
2581void MacroAssembler::li(Register dst, Handle<HeapObject> value,
2582 RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
2583 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2584 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
2585 // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
2586 // embedding the relocatable value.
2587 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
2588 IndirectLoadConstant(dst, value);
2589 return;
2590 } else {
2591 li(dst, Operand(value, rmode));
2592 }
2593}
2594
2595void MacroAssembler::li(Register dst, ExternalReference reference,
2596 LiFlags mode) {
2597 if (root_array_available()) {
2598 if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
2599 AddWord(dst, kRootRegister,
2600 Operand(reference.offset_from_root_register()));
2601 return;
2602 }
2603 if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
2604 IndirectLoadExternalReference(dst, reference);
2605 return;
2606 }
2607 }
2608 // External references should not get created with IDs if
2609 // `!root_array_available()`.
2610 CHECK(!reference.IsIsolateFieldId());
2611 li(dst, Operand(reference), mode);
2612}
2613
2614static inline int InstrCountForLiLower32Bit(int64_t value) {
2615 int64_t Hi20 = ((value + 0x800) >> 12);
2616 int64_t Lo12 = value << 52 >> 52;
2617 if (Hi20 == 0 || Lo12 == 0) {
2618 return 1;
2619 }
2620 return 2;
2621}
2622
2623int MacroAssembler::InstrCountForLi64Bit(int64_t value) {
2624 if (is_int32(value + 0x800)) {
2625 return InstrCountForLiLower32Bit(value);
2626 } else {
2627 return RV_li_count(value);
2628 }
2629 UNREACHABLE();
2630 return INT_MAX;
2631}
2632
2633void MacroAssembler::li_optimized(Register rd, Operand j, LiFlags mode) {
2634 DCHECK(!j.is_reg());
2635 DCHECK(!MustUseReg(j.rmode()));
2636 DCHECK(mode == OPTIMIZE_SIZE);
2637 Li(rd, j.immediate());
2638}
2639
2640void MacroAssembler::li(Register rd, Operand j, LiFlags mode) {
2641 DCHECK(!j.is_reg());
2642 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2643 if (!MustUseReg(j.rmode()) && mode == OPTIMIZE_SIZE) {
2644 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2645 int count = RV_li_count(j.immediate(), temps.CanAcquire());
2646 int reverse_count = RV_li_count(~j.immediate(), temps.CanAcquire());
2647 if (v8_flags.riscv_constant_pool && count >= 4 && reverse_count >= 4) {
2648 // Ld/Lw an Address from a constant pool.
2649#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2650 RecordEntry((uint32_t)j.immediate(), j.rmode());
2651#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2652 RecordEntry((uint64_t)j.immediate(), j.rmode());
2653#endif
2654 auipc(rd, 0);
2655 // Record a value into constant pool, passing 1 as the offset makes the
2656 // promise that LoadWord() generates full 32-bit instruction to be
2657 // patched with real value in the future
2658 LoadWord(rd, MemOperand(rd, 1));
2659 } else {
2660 if ((count - reverse_count) > 1) {
2661 Li(rd, ~j.immediate());
2662 not_(rd, rd);
2663 } else {
2664 Li(rd, j.immediate());
2665 }
2666 }
2667 } else if (MustUseReg(j.rmode())) {
2668 int64_t immediate;
2669 if (RelocInfo::IsWasmCanonicalSigId(j.rmode()) ||
2670 RelocInfo::IsWasmCodePointerTableEntry(j.rmode()) ||
2671 RelocInfo::IsJSDispatchHandle(j.rmode())) {
2672 // These reloc datas are 32-bit values.
2673 DCHECK(is_int32(j.immediate()) || is_uint32(j.immediate()));
2674 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2675#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2676 li_constant32(rd, int32_t(j.immediate()));
2677#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2678 li_constant(rd, int32_t(j.immediate()));
2679#endif
2680 return;
2681 } else if (RelocInfo::IsCompressedEmbeddedObject(j.rmode())) {
2682 Handle<HeapObject> handle(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(j.immediate()));
2683 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(handle);
2684 DCHECK(is_uint32(index));
2685 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2686#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2687 li_constant32(rd, static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
2688#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2689 li_constant(rd, index);
2690#endif
2691 return;
2692 } else if (RelocInfo::IsFullEmbeddedObject(j.rmode())) {
2693 if (j.IsHeapNumberRequest()) {
2694 RequestHeapNumber(j.heap_number_request());
2695 immediate = j.immediate_for_heap_number_request();
2696 } else {
2697 immediate = j.immediate();
2698 }
2699#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2700 BlockPoolsScope block_pools(this);
2701 Handle<HeapObject> handle(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(immediate));
2702 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(handle);
2703 if (RecordEntry(static_cast<uint64_t>(index), j.rmode()) ==
2704 RelocInfoStatus::kMustRecord) {
2705 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode(), index);
2706 }
2707 DEBUG_PRINTF("\t EmbeddedObjectIndex%lu\n", index);
2708 auipc(rd, 0);
2709 // Record a value into constant pool, passing 1 as the offset makes the
2710 // promise that LoadWord() generates full 32-bit instruction to be
2711 // patched with real value in the future
2712 LoadWord(rd, MemOperand(rd, 1));
2713#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2714 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2715 li_constant(rd, immediate);
2716#endif
2717 return;
2718 } else {
2719 immediate = j.immediate();
2720 }
2721 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode(), immediate);
2722 li_ptr(rd, immediate);
2723 } else if (mode == ADDRESS_LOAD) {
2724 // We always need the same number of instructions as we may need to patch
2725 // this code to load another value which may need all 6 instructions.
2726 RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2727 li_ptr(rd, j.immediate());
2728 } else { // Always emit the same 48 bit instruction
2729 // sequence.
2730 li_ptr(rd, j.immediate());
2731 }
2732}
2733
2734static RegList t_regs = {t0, t1, t2, t3, t4, t5, t6};
2735static RegList a_regs = {a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7};
2736static RegList s_regs = {s1, s2, s3, s4, s5, s6, s7, s8, s9, s10, s11};
2737
2738void MacroAssembler::MultiPush(RegList regs) {
2739 int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
2740 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kSystemPointerSize;
2741
2742#define TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(reg) \
2743 if (regs.has(reg)) { \
2744 stack_offset -= kSystemPointerSize; \
2745 StoreWord(reg, MemOperand(sp, stack_offset)); \
2746 regs.clear(reg); \
2747 }
2748
2749#define T_REGS(V) V(t6) V(t5) V(t4) V(t3) V(t2) V(t1) V(t0)
2750#define A_REGS(V) V(a7) V(a6) V(a5) V(a4) V(a3) V(a2) V(a1) V(a0)
2751#define S_REGS(V) \
2752 V(s11) V(s10) V(s9) V(s8) V(s7) V(s6) V(s5) V(s4) V(s3) V(s2) V(s1)
2753
2754 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_offset));
2755
2756 // Certain usage of MultiPush requires that registers are pushed onto the
2757 // stack in a particular: ra, fp, sp, gp, .... (basically in the decreasing
2758 // order of register numbers according to MIPS register numbers)
2759 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(ra);
2760 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(fp);
2761 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(sp);
2762 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(gp);
2763 TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(tp);
2764 if (!(regs & s_regs).is_empty()) {
2765 S_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2766 }
2767 if (!(regs & a_regs).is_empty()) {
2768 A_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2769 }
2770 if (!(regs & t_regs).is_empty()) {
2771 T_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2772 }
2773
2774 DCHECK(regs.is_empty());
2775
2776#undef TEST_AND_PUSH_REG
2777#undef T_REGS
2778#undef A_REGS
2779#undef S_REGS
2780}
2781
2782void MacroAssembler::MultiPop(RegList regs) {
2783 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
2784
2785#define TEST_AND_POP_REG(reg) \
2786 if (regs.has(reg)) { \
2787 LoadWord(reg, MemOperand(sp, stack_offset)); \
2788 stack_offset += kSystemPointerSize; \
2789 regs.clear(reg); \
2790 }
2791
2792#define T_REGS(V) V(t0) V(t1) V(t2) V(t3) V(t4) V(t5) V(t6)
2793#define A_REGS(V) V(a0) V(a1) V(a2) V(a3) V(a4) V(a5) V(a6) V(a7)
2794#define S_REGS(V) \
2795 V(s1) V(s2) V(s3) V(s4) V(s5) V(s6) V(s7) V(s8) V(s9) V(s10) V(s11)
2796
2797 // MultiPop pops from the stack in reverse order as MultiPush
2798 if (!(regs & t_regs).is_empty()) {
2799 T_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2800 }
2801 if (!(regs & a_regs).is_empty()) {
2802 A_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2803 }
2804 if (!(regs & s_regs).is_empty()) {
2805 S_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2806 }
2807 TEST_AND_POP_REG(tp);
2808 TEST_AND_POP_REG(gp);
2809 TEST_AND_POP_REG(sp);
2810 TEST_AND_POP_REG(fp);
2811 TEST_AND_POP_REG(ra);
2812
2813 DCHECK(regs.is_empty());
2814
2815 addi(sp, sp, stack_offset);
2816
2817#undef TEST_AND_POP_REG
2818#undef T_REGS
2819#undef S_REGS
2820#undef A_REGS
2821}
2822
2823void MacroAssembler::MultiPushFPU(DoubleRegList regs) {
2824 int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
2825 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kDoubleSize;
2826
2827 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_offset));
2828 for (int16_t i = kNumRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
2829 if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
2830 stack_offset -= kDoubleSize;
2831 StoreDouble(FPURegister::from_code(i), MemOperand(sp, stack_offset));
2832 }
2833 }
2834}
2835
2836void MacroAssembler::MultiPopFPU(DoubleRegList regs) {
2837 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
2838
2839 for (int16_t i = 0; i < kNumRegisters; i++) {
2840 if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
2841 LoadDouble(FPURegister::from_code(i), MemOperand(sp, stack_offset));
2842 stack_offset += kDoubleSize;
2843 }
2844 }
2845 addi(sp, sp, stack_offset);
2846}
2847
2848#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2849void MacroAssembler::AddPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2850 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2851 Register right_low, Register right_high,
2852 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2853 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2854 Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2855 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2856
2857 Add32(scratch1, left_low, right_low);
2858 // Save the carry
2859 Sltu(scratch3, scratch1, left_low);
2860 Add32(scratch2, left_high, right_high);
2861
2862 // Output higher 32 bits + carry
2863 Add32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2864 Move(dst_low, scratch1);
2865}
2866
2867void MacroAssembler::SubPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2868 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2869 Register right_low, Register right_high,
2870 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2871 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2872 Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2873 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2874
2875 // Check if we need a borrow
2876 Sltu(scratch3, left_low, right_low);
2877 Sub32(scratch1, left_low, right_low);
2878 Sub32(scratch2, left_high, right_high);
2879
2880 // Output higher 32 bits - borrow
2881 Sub32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2882 Move(dst_low, scratch1);
2883}
2884
2885void MacroAssembler::AndPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2886 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2887 Register right_low, Register right_high) {
2888 And(dst_low, left_low, right_low);
2889 And(dst_high, left_high, right_high);
2890}
2891
2892void MacroAssembler::OrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2893 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2894 Register right_low, Register right_high) {
2895 Or(dst_low, left_low, right_low);
2896 Or(dst_high, left_high, right_high);
2897}
2898void MacroAssembler::XorPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2899 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2900 Register right_low, Register right_high) {
2901 Xor(dst_low, left_low, right_low);
2902 Xor(dst_high, left_high, right_high);
2903}
2904
2905void MacroAssembler::MulPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2906 Register left_low, Register left_high,
2907 Register right_low, Register right_high,
2908 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2909 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2910 Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2911 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2912 if (dst_low == right_low) {
2913 mv(scratch1, right_low);
2914 }
2915 Mul(scratch3, left_low, right_high);
2916 // NOTE: do not move these around, recommended sequence is MULH-MUL
2917 // LL * RL : higher 32 bits
2918 mulhu(scratch2, left_low, right_low);
2919 // LL * RL : lower 32 bits
2920 Mul(dst_low, left_low, right_low);
2921 // (LL * RH) + (LL * RL : higher 32 bits)
2922 Add32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch3);
2923 if (dst_low != right_low) {
2924 Mul(scratch3, left_high, right_low);
2925 } else {
2926 Mul(scratch3, left_high, scratch1);
2927 }
2928 Add32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2929}
2930
2931void MacroAssembler::ShlPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2932 Register src_low, Register src_high,
2933 Register shift, Register scratch1,
2934 Register scratch2) {
2935 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2936 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2937 Label done;
2938 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2939 Register scratch3 = no_reg;
2940 if (dst_low == src_low) {
2941 scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2942 mv(scratch3, src_low);
2943 }
2944 And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
2945 // LOW32 << shamt
2946 sll(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
2947 // HIGH32 << shamt
2948 sll(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
2949
2950 // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
2951 Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
2952
2953 // LOW32 >> (32 - shamt)
2954 li(scratch2, 32);
2955 Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2956 if (dst_low == src_low) {
2957 srl(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
2958 } else {
2959 srl(scratch1, src_low, scratch2);
2960 }
2961
2962 // (HIGH32 << shamt) | (LOW32 >> (32 - shamt))
2963 Or(dst_high, dst_high, scratch1);
2964
2965 // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
2966 // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
2967 // is set
2968 And(scratch1, shift, 32);
2969 Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
2970 Move(dst_high, dst_low);
2971 Move(dst_low, zero_reg);
2972
2973 bind(&done);
2974}
2975
2976void MacroAssembler::ShlPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2977 Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
2978 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2979 DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
2980 DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_low);
2981 DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_low);
2982 shift &= 0x3F;
2983 if (shift == 0) {
2984 Move(dst_high, src_high);
2985 Move(dst_low, src_low);
2986 } else if (shift == 32) {
2987 Move(dst_high, src_low);
2988 li(dst_low, Operand(0));
2989 } else if (shift > 32) {
2990 shift &= 0x1F;
2991 slli(dst_high, src_low, shift);
2992 li(dst_low, Operand(0));
2993 } else {
2994 slli(dst_high, src_high, shift);
2995 slli(dst_low, src_low, shift);
2996 srli(scratch1, src_low, 32 - shift);
2997 Or(dst_high, dst_high, scratch1);
2998 }
2999}
3000
3001void MacroAssembler::ShrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3002 Register src_low, Register src_high,
3003 Register shift, Register scratch1,
3004 Register scratch2) {
3005 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3006 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3007 Label done;
3008 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3009 Register scratch3 = no_reg;
3010 if (dst_high == src_high) {
3011 scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
3012 mv(scratch3, src_high);
3013 }
3014 And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
3015 // HIGH32 >> shamt
3016 srl(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
3017 // LOW32 >> shamt
3018 srl(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
3019
3020 // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
3021 Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
3022
3023 // HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)
3024 li(scratch2, 32);
3025 Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
3026 if (dst_high == src_high) {
3027 sll(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
3028 } else {
3029 sll(scratch1, src_high, scratch2);
3030 }
3031
3032 // (HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)) | (LOW32 >> shamt)
3033 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3034
3035 // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
3036 // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
3037 // is set
3038 And(scratch1, shift, 32);
3039 Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
3040 Move(dst_low, dst_high);
3041 Move(dst_high, zero_reg);
3042
3043 bind(&done);
3044}
3045
3046void MacroAssembler::ShrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3047 Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
3048 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
3049 DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
3050 DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_high);
3051 DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_high);
3052 shift &= 0x3F;
3053 if (shift == 32) {
3054 mv(dst_low, src_high);
3055 li(dst_high, Operand(0));
3056 } else if (shift > 32) {
3057 shift &= 0x1F;
3058 srli(dst_low, src_high, shift);
3059 li(dst_high, Operand(0));
3060 } else if (shift == 0) {
3061 Move(dst_low, src_low);
3062 Move(dst_high, src_high);
3063 } else {
3064 srli(dst_low, src_low, shift);
3065 srli(dst_high, src_high, shift);
3066 slli(scratch1, src_high, 32 - shift);
3067 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3068 }
3069}
3070
3071void MacroAssembler::SarPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3072 Register src_low, Register src_high,
3073 Register shift, Register scratch1,
3074 Register scratch2) {
3075 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3076 Label done;
3077 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3078 Register scratch3 = no_reg;
3079 if (dst_high == src_high) {
3080 scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
3081 mv(scratch3, src_high);
3082 }
3083 And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
3084 // HIGH32 >> shamt (arithmetic)
3085 sra(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
3086 // LOW32 >> shamt (logical)
3087 srl(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
3088
3089 // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
3090 Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
3091
3092 // HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)
3093 li(scratch2, 32);
3094 Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
3095 if (dst_high == src_high) {
3096 sll(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
3097 } else {
3098 sll(scratch1, src_high, scratch2);
3099 }
3100 // (HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)) | (LOW32 >> shamt)
3101 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3102
3103 // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
3104 // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
3105 // is set
3106 And(scratch1, shift, 32);
3107 Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
3108 Move(dst_low, dst_high);
3109 Sra32(dst_high, dst_high, 31);
3110
3111 bind(&done);
3112}
3113
3114void MacroAssembler::SarPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3115 Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
3116 Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
3117 DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
3118 DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_high);
3119 DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_high);
3120 shift = shift & 0x3F;
3121 if (shift == 0) {
3122 mv(dst_low, src_low);
3123 mv(dst_high, src_high);
3124 } else if (shift < 32) {
3125 srli(dst_low, src_low, shift);
3126 srai(dst_high, src_high, shift);
3127 slli(scratch1, src_high, 32 - shift);
3128 Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3129 } else if (shift == 32) {
3130 srai(dst_high, src_high, 31);
3131 mv(dst_low, src_high);
3132 } else {
3133 srai(dst_high, src_high, 31);
3134 srai(dst_low, src_high, shift - 32);
3135 }
3136}
3137#endif
3138
3139void MacroAssembler::ExtractBits(Register rt, Register rs, uint16_t pos,
3140 uint16_t size, bool sign_extend) {
3141#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3142 DCHECK(pos < 64 && 0 < size && size <= 64 && 0 < pos + size &&
3143 pos + size <= 64);
3144 slli(rt, rs, 64 - (pos + size));
3145 if (sign_extend) {
3146 srai(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3147 } else {
3148 srli(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3149 }
3150#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3151 DCHECK_LT(pos, 32);
3152 DCHECK_GT(size, 0);
3153 DCHECK_LE(size, 32);
3154 DCHECK_GT(pos + size, 0);
3155 DCHECK_LE(pos + size, 32);
3156 slli(rt, rs, 32 - (pos + size));
3157 if (sign_extend) {
3158 srai(rt, rt, 32 - size);
3159 } else {
3160 srli(rt, rt, 32 - size);
3161 }
3162#endif
3163}
3164
3165void MacroAssembler::InsertBits(Register dest, Register source, Register pos,
3166 int size) {
3167#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3168 DCHECK_LT(size, 64);
3169#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3170 DCHECK_LT(size, 32);
3171#endif
3172 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3173 Register mask = temps.Acquire();
3174 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3175 Register source_ = temps.Acquire();
3176 // Create a mask of the length=size.
3177 li(mask, 1);
3178 slli(mask, mask, size);
3179 addi(mask, mask, -1);
3180 and_(source_, mask, source);
3181 sll(source_, source_, pos);
3182 // Make a mask containing 0's. 0's start at "pos" with length=size.
3183 sll(mask, mask, pos);
3184 not_(mask, mask);
3185 // cut area for insertion of source.
3186 and_(dest, mask, dest);
3187 // insert source
3188 or_(dest, dest, source_);
3189}

3225template <typename CvtFunc>
3226void MacroAssembler::RoundFloatingPointToInteger(Register rd, FPURegister fs,
3227 Register result,
3228 CvtFunc fcvt_generator) {
3229 // Save csr_fflags to scratch & clear exception flags
3230 if (result.is_valid()) {
3231 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3232 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3233 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3234
3235 int exception_flags = kInvalidOperation;
3236 csrrci(scratch, csr_fflags, exception_flags);
3237
3238 // actual conversion instruction
3239 fcvt_generator(this, rd, fs);
3240
3241 // check kInvalidOperation flag (out-of-range, NaN)
3242 // set result to 1 if normal, otherwise set result to 0 for abnormal
3243 frflags(result);
3244 andi(result, result, exception_flags);
3245 seqz(result, result); // result <-- 1 (normal), result <-- 0 (abnormal)
3246
3247 // restore csr_fflags
3248 csrw(csr_fflags, scratch);
3249 } else {
3250 // actual conversion instruction
3251 fcvt_generator(this, rd, fs);
3252 }
3253}
3254
3255void MacroAssembler::Clear_if_nan_d(Register rd, FPURegister fs) {
3256 Label no_nan;
3257 DCHECK_NE(kScratchReg, rd);
3258 feq_d(kScratchReg, fs, fs);
3259 bnez(kScratchReg, &no_nan);
3260 Move(rd, zero_reg);
3261 bind(&no_nan);
3262}
3263
3264void MacroAssembler::Clear_if_nan_s(Register rd, FPURegister fs) {

3267 feq_s(kScratchReg, fs, fs);
3268 bnez(kScratchReg, &no_nan);
3269 Move(rd, zero_reg);
3270 bind(&no_nan);
3271}

3370
3371// According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3372// the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3373// rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3374// round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3375// handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3376#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3377template <typename F>
3378void MacroAssembler::RoundHelper(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src,
3379 FPURegister fpu_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm) {
3380 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3381 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3382 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3383
3384 DCHECK((std::is_same<float, F>::value) || (std::is_same<double, F>::value));
3385 // Need at least two FPRs, so check against dst == src == fpu_scratch
3386 DCHECK(!(dst == src && dst == fpu_scratch));
3387
3388 const int kFloatMantissaBits =
3389 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32MantissaBits : kFloat64MantissaBits;
3390 const int kFloatExponentBits =
3391 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBits : kFloat64ExponentBits;
3392 const int kFloatExponentBias =
3393 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBias : kFloat64ExponentBias;
3394 Label done;
3395
3396 {
3397 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3398 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3399 // extract exponent value of the source floating-point to scratch
3400 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3401 fmv_x_d(scratch, src);
3402 } else {
3403 fmv_x_w(scratch, src);
3404 }
3405 ExtractBits(scratch2, scratch, kFloatMantissaBits, kFloatExponentBits);
3406 }
3407
3408 // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3409 // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3410 // generating another branch)
3411 if (dst != src) {
3412 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3413 fmv_d(dst, src);
3414 } else {
3415 fmv_s(dst, src);
3416 }
3417 }
3418 {
3419 Label not_NaN;
3420 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3421 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3422 // According to the wasm spec
3423 // (https://webassembly.github.io/spec/core/exec/numerics.html#aux-nans)
3424 // if input is canonical NaN, then output is canonical NaN, and if input is
3425 // any other NaN, then output is any NaN with most significant bit of
3426 // payload is 1. In RISC-V, feq_d will set scratch to 0 if src is a NaN. If
3427 // src is not a NaN, branch to the label and do nothing, but if it is,
3428 // fmin_d will set dst to the canonical NaN.
3429 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3430 feq_d(scratch, src, src);
3431 bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3432 fmin_d(dst, src, src);
3433 } else {
3434 feq_s(scratch, src, src);
3435 bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3436 fmin_s(dst, src, src);
3437 }
3438 bind(&not_NaN);
3439 }
3440
3441 // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3442 // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3443 // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3444 // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3445 // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3446 // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3447 // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3448 Branch(&done, greater_equal, scratch2,
3449 Operand(kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits));
3450
3451 // Actual rounding is needed along this path
3452
3453 // old_src holds the original input, needed for the case of src == dst
3454 FPURegister old_src = src;
3455 if (src == dst) {
3456 DCHECK(fpu_scratch != dst);
3457 Move(fpu_scratch, src);
3458 old_src = fpu_scratch;
3459 }
3460
3461 // Since only input whose real exponent value is less than kMantissaBits
3462 // (i.e., 23 or 52-bits) falls into this path, the value range of the input
3463 // falls into that of 23- or 53-bit integers. So we round the input to integer
3464 // values, then convert them back to floating-point.
3465 {
3466 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3467 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3468 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3469 fcvt_l_d(scratch, src, frm);
3470 fcvt_d_l(dst, scratch, frm);
3471 } else {
3472 fcvt_w_s(scratch, src, frm);
3473 fcvt_s_w(dst, scratch, frm);
3474 }
3475 }
3476 // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3477 // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3478 // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3479 // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3480 // Therefore, we use sign-bit injection to produce +/-0 correctly. Instead of
3481 // testing for zero w/ a branch, we just insert sign-bit for everyone on this
3482 // path (this is where old_src is needed)
3483 if (std::is_same<F, double>::value) {
3484 fsgnj_d(dst, dst, old_src);
3485 } else {
3486 fsgnj_s(dst, dst, old_src);
3487 }
3488
3489 bind(&done);
3490}
3491#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3492// According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3493// the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3494// rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3495// round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3496// handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3497void MacroAssembler::RoundFloat(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src,
3498 FPURegister fpu_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm) {
3499 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3500 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3501 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3502
3503 // Need at least two FPRs, so check against dst == src == fpu_scratch
3504 DCHECK(!(dst == src && dst == fpu_scratch));
3505
3506 const int kFloatMantissaBits = kFloat32MantissaBits;
3507 const int kFloatExponentBits = kFloat32ExponentBits;
3508 const int kFloatExponentBias = kFloat32ExponentBias;
3509 Label done;
3510
3511 {
3512 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3513 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3514 // extract exponent value of the source floating-point to scratch
3515 fmv_x_w(scratch, src);
3516 ExtractBits(scratch2, scratch, kFloatMantissaBits, kFloatExponentBits);
3517 }
3518
3519 // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3520 // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3521 // generating another branch)
3522 if (dst != src) {
3523 fmv_s(dst, src);
3524 }
3525 {
3526 Label not_NaN;
3527 UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3528 Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3529 // According to the wasm spec
3530 // (https://webassembly.github.io/spec/core/exec/numerics.html#aux-nans)
3531 // if input is canonical NaN, then output is canonical NaN, and if input is
3532 // any other NaN, then output is any NaN with most significant bit of
3533 // payload is 1. In RISC-V, feq_d will set scratch to 0 if src is a NaN. If
3534 // src is not a NaN, branch to the label and do nothing, but if it is,
3535 // fmin_d will set dst to the canonical NaN.
3536 feq_s(scratch, src, src);
3537 bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3538 fmin_s(dst, src, src);
3539 bind(&not_NaN);
3540 }
3541
3542 // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3543 // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3544 // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3545 // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3546 // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3547 // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3548 // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3549 Branch(&done, greater_equal, scratch2,
3550 Operand(kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits));
3551
3552 // Actual rounding is needed along this path
3553
3554 // old_src holds the original input, needed for the case of src == dst
3555 FPURegister old_src = src;
3556 if (src == dst) {
3557 DCHECK(fpu_scratch != dst);
3558 Move(fpu_scratch, src);
3559 old_src = fpu_scratch;
3560 }
3561
3562 // Since only input whose real exponent value is less than kMantissaBits
3563 // (i.e., 23 or 52-bits) falls into this path, the value range of the input
3564 // falls into that of 23- or 53-bit integers. So we round the input to integer
3565 // values, then convert them back to floating-point.
3566 {
3567 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3568 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3569 fcvt_w_s(scratch, src, frm);
3570 fcvt_s_w(dst, scratch, frm);
3571 }
3572 // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3573 // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3574 // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3575 // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3576 // Therefore, we use sign-bit injection to produce +/-0 correctly. Instead of
3577 // testing for zero w/ a branch, we just insert sign-bit for everyone on this
3578 // path (this is where old_src is needed)
3579 fsgnj_s(dst, dst, old_src);
3580
3581 bind(&done);
3582}
3583#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3584// According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3585// the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3586// rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3587// round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3588// handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3589template <typename F>
3590void MacroAssembler::RoundHelper(VRegister dst, VRegister src, Register scratch,
3591 VRegister v_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm,
3592 bool keep_nan_same) {
3593 VU.set(scratch, std::is_same<F, float>::value ? E32 : E64, m1);
3594 // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3595 // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3596 // generating another branch)
3597
3598 // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3599 // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3600 // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3601 // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3602 // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3603 // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3604 // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3605 const int kFloatMantissaBits =
3606 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32MantissaBits : kFloat64MantissaBits;
3607 const int kFloatExponentBits =
3608 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBits : kFloat64ExponentBits;
3609 const int kFloatExponentBias =
3610 sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBias : kFloat64ExponentBias;
3611
3612 // slli(rt, rs, 64 - (pos + size));
3613 // if (sign_extend) {
3614 // srai(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3615 // } else {
3616 // srli(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3617 // }
3618 vmv_vx(v_scratch, zero_reg);
3619 li(scratch, 64 - kFloatMantissaBits - kFloatExponentBits);
3620 vsll_vx(v_scratch, src, scratch);
3621 li(scratch, 64 - kFloatExponentBits);
3622 vsrl_vx(v_scratch, v_scratch, scratch);
3623 li(scratch, kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits);
3624 vmslt_vx(v0, v_scratch, scratch);
3625 VU.set(frm);
3626 vmv_vv(dst, src);
3627 if (dst == src) {
3628 vmv_vv(v_scratch, src);
3629 }
3630 vfcvt_x_f_v(dst, src, MaskType::Mask);
3631 vfcvt_f_x_v(dst, dst, MaskType::Mask);
3632
3633 // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3634 // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3635 // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3636 // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3637 if (dst == src) {
3638 vfsngj_vv(dst, dst, v_scratch);
3639 } else {
3640 vfsngj_vv(dst, dst, src);
3641 }
3642 if (!keep_nan_same) {
3643 vmfeq_vv(v0, src, src);
3644 vnot_vv(v0, v0);
3645 if (std::is_same<F, float>::value) {
3646 fmv_w_x(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3647 } else {
3648#ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3649 fmv_d_x(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3650#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3651 fcvt_d_w(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3652#endif
3653 }
3654 vfadd_vf(dst, src, kScratchDoubleReg, MaskType::Mask);
3655 }
3656}
3657
3658void MacroAssembler::Ceil_f(VRegister vdst, VRegister vsrc, Register scratch,
3659 VRegister v_scratch) {
3660 RoundHelper<float>(vdst, vsrc, scratch, v_scratch, RUP, false);
3661}
