3776void MacroAssembler::CompareF32(Register rd, FPUCondition cc, FPURegister cmp1,
3777 FPURegister cmp2) {
3778 switch (cc) {
3779 case EQ:
3780 feq_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3781 break;
3782 case NE:
3783 feq_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3784 NegateBool(rd, rd);
3785 break;
3786 case LT:
3787 flt_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3788 break;
3789 case GE:
3790 fle_s(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3791 break;
3792 case LE:
3793 fle_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3794 break;
3795 case GT:
3796 flt_s(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3797 break;
3798 default:
3799 UNREACHABLE();
3800 }
3801}
3802
3803void MacroAssembler::CompareF64(Register rd, FPUCondition cc, FPURegister cmp1,
3804 FPURegister cmp2) {
3805 switch (cc) {
3806 case EQ:
3807 feq_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3808 break;
3809 case NE:
3810 feq_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3811 NegateBool(rd, rd);
3812 break;
3813 case LT:
3814 flt_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3815 break;
3816 case GE:
3817 fle_d(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3818 break;
3819 case LE:
3820 fle_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3821 break;
3822 case GT:
3823 flt_d(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3824 break;
3825 default:
3826 UNREACHABLE();
3827 }
3828}
3829
3830void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNotNanF32(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3831 FPURegister cmp2) {
3832 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3833 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3834 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3835
3836 feq_s(rd, cmp1, cmp1); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1)
3837 feq_s(scratch, cmp2, cmp2); // scratch <- !isNaN(cmp2)
3838 And(rd, rd, scratch); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3839}
3840
3841void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNotNanF64(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3842 FPURegister cmp2) {
3843 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3844 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3845 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3846
3847 feq_d(rd, cmp1, cmp1); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1)
3848 feq_d(scratch, cmp2, cmp2); // scratch <- !isNaN(cmp2)
3849 And(rd, rd, scratch); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3850}
3851
3852void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF32(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3853 FPURegister cmp2) {
3854 CompareIsNotNanF32(rd, cmp1, cmp2); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3855 Xor(rd, rd, 1); // rd <- isNan(cmp1) || isNan(cmp2)
3856}
3857
3858void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF64(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3859 FPURegister cmp2) {
3860 CompareIsNotNanF64(rd, cmp1, cmp2); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3861 Xor(rd, rd, 1); // rd <- isNan(cmp1) || isNan(cmp2)
3862}
3863
3864void MacroAssembler::BranchTrueShortF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3865 Branch(target, not_equal, rs, Operand(zero_reg));
3866}
3867
3868void MacroAssembler::BranchFalseShortF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3869 Branch(target, equal, rs, Operand(zero_reg));
3870}
3871
3872void MacroAssembler::BranchTrueF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3873 bool long_branch =
3874 target->is_bound() ? !is_near(target) : is_trampoline_emitted();
3875 if (long_branch) {
3876 Label skip;
3877 BranchFalseShortF(rs, &skip);
3878 BranchLong(target);
3879 bind(&skip);
3880 } else {
3881 BranchTrueShortF(rs, target);
3882 }
3883}
3884
3885void MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3886 bool long_branch =
3887 target->is_bound() ? !is_near(target) : is_trampoline_emitted();
3888 if (long_branch) {
3889 Label skip;
3890 BranchTrueShortF(rs, &skip);
3891 BranchLong(target);
3892 bind(&skip);
3893 } else {
3894 BranchFalseShortF(rs, target);
3895 }
3896}
3897
3898void MacroAssembler::InsertHighWordF64(FPURegister dst, Register src_high) {
3899#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3900 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3901 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3902 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3903 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3904
3905 DCHECK(src_high != scratch2 && src_high != scratch);
3906
3907 fmv_x_d(scratch, dst);
3908 slli(scratch2, src_high, 32);
3909 slli(scratch, scratch, 32);
3910 srli(scratch, scratch, 32);
3911 or_(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
3912 fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);
3913#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3914 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3915 Add32(sp, sp, Operand(-8));
3916 StoreDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3917 Sw(src_high, MemOperand(sp, 4));
3918 LoadDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3919 Add32(sp, sp, Operand(8));
3920#endif
3921}
3922
3923void MacroAssembler::InsertLowWordF64(FPURegister dst, Register src_low) {
3924#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3925 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3926 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3927 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3928 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3929
3930 DCHECK(src_low != scratch && src_low != scratch2);
3931 fmv_x_d(scratch, dst);
3932 slli(scratch2, src_low, 32);
3933 srli(scratch2, scratch2, 32);
3934 srli(scratch, scratch, 32);
3935 slli(scratch, scratch, 32);
3936 or_(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
3937 fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);
3938#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3939 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3940 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(-8));
3941 StoreDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3942 Sw(src_low, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3943 LoadDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3944 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(8));
3945#endif
3946}
3947
3948void MacroAssembler::LoadFPRImmediate(FPURegister dst, uint32_t src) {
3949 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3950 // Handle special values first.
3951 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f) && has_single_zero_reg_set_) {
3952 if (dst != kSingleRegZero) fmv_s(dst, kSingleRegZero);
3953 } else if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(-0.0f) &&
3954 has_single_zero_reg_set_) {
3955 Neg_s(dst, kSingleRegZero);
3956 } else {
3957 if (dst == kSingleRegZero) {
3958 DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f));
3959 fcvt_s_w(dst, zero_reg);
3960 has_single_zero_reg_set_ = true;
3961 } else {
3962 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f)) {
3963 fcvt_s_w(dst, zero_reg);
3964 } else {
3965 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3966 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3967 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(src)));
3968 fmv_w_x(dst, scratch);
3969 }
3970 }
3971 }
3972}
3973
3974void MacroAssembler::LoadFPRImmediate(FPURegister dst, uint64_t src) {
3975 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3976 // Handle special values first.
3977 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0) && has_double_zero_reg_set_) {
3978 if (dst != kDoubleRegZero) fmv_d(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
3979 } else if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(-0.0) &&
3980 has_double_zero_reg_set_) {
3981 Neg_d(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
3982 } else {
3983#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3984 if (dst == kDoubleRegZero) {
3985 DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0));
3986 fcvt_d_l(dst, zero_reg);
3987 has_double_zero_reg_set_ = true;
3988 } else {
3989 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3990 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3991 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0)) {
3992 fcvt_d_l(dst, zero_reg);
3993 } else {
3994 li(scratch, Operand(src));
3995 fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);
3996 }
3997 }
3998#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3999 if (dst == kDoubleRegZero) {
4000 DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0));
4001 fcvt_d_w(dst, zero_reg);
4002 has_double_zero_reg_set_ = true;
4003 } else {
4004 // Todo: need to clear the stack content?
4005 if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0)) {
4006 fcvt_d_w(dst, zero_reg);
4007 } else {
4008 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4009 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4010 uint32_t low_32 = src & 0xffffffffull;
4011 uint32_t up_32 = src >> 32;
4012 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(-8));
4013 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(low_32)));
4014 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4015 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(up_32)));
4016 Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
4017 LoadDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4018 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(8));
4019 }
4020 }
4021#endif
4022 }
4023}
4024
4025void MacroAssembler::CompareI(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
4026 Condition cond) {
4027 switch (cond) {
4028 case eq:
4029 Seq(rd, rs, rt);
4030 break;
4031 case ne:
4032 Sne(rd, rs, rt);
4033 break;
4034
4035 // Signed comparison.
4036 case greater:
4037 Sgt(rd, rs, rt);
4038 break;
4039 case greater_equal:
4040 Sge(rd, rs, rt); // rs >= rt
4041 break;
4042 case less:
4043 Slt(rd, rs, rt); // rs < rt
4044 break;
4045 case less_equal:
4046 Sle(rd, rs, rt); // rs <= rt
4047 break;
4048
4049 // Unsigned comparison.
4050 case Ugreater:
4051 Sgtu(rd, rs, rt); // rs > rt
4052 break;
4053 case Ugreater_equal:
4054 Sgeu(rd, rs, rt); // rs >= rt
4055 break;
4056 case Uless:
4057 Sltu(rd, rs, rt); // rs < rt
4058 break;
4059 case Uless_equal:
4060 Sleu(rd, rs, rt); // rs <= rt
4061 break;
4062 case cc_always:
4063 UNREACHABLE();
4064 default:
4065 UNREACHABLE();
4066 }
4067}
4068
4069// dest <- (condition != 0 ? zero : dest)
4070void MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfConditionNotZero(Register dest,
4071 Register condition) {
4072 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZICOND)) {
4073 czero_nez(dest, dest, condition);
4074 } else {
4075 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4076 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4077 seqz(scratch, condition);
4078 // neg + and may be more efficient than mul(dest, dest, scratch)
4079 neg(scratch, scratch); // 0 is still 0, 1 becomes all 1s
4080 and_(dest, dest, scratch);
4081 }
4082}
4083
4084// dest <- (condition == 0 ? 0 : dest)
4085void MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfConditionZero(Register dest,
4086 Register condition) {
4087 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZICOND)) {
4088 czero_eqz(dest, dest, condition);
4089 } else {
4090 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4091 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4092 snez(scratch, condition);
4093 // neg + and may be more efficient than mul(dest, dest, scratch);
4094 neg(scratch, scratch); // 0 is still 0, 1 becomes all 1s
4095 and_(dest, dest, scratch);
4096 }
4097}
4098
4099void MacroAssembler::Clz32(Register rd, Register xx) {
4100 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4101#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4102 clzw(rd, xx);
4103#else
4104 clz(rd, xx);
4105#endif
4106 } else {
4107 // 32 bit unsigned in lower word: count number of leading zeros.
4108 // int n = 32;
4109 // unsigned y;
4110
4111 // y = x >>16; if (y != 0) { n = n -16; x = y; }
4112 // y = x >> 8; if (y != 0) { n = n - 8; x = y; }
4113 // y = x >> 4; if (y != 0) { n = n - 4; x = y; }
4114 // y = x >> 2; if (y != 0) { n = n - 2; x = y; }
4115 // y = x >> 1; if (y != 0) {rd = n - 2; return;}
4116 // rd = n - x;
4117
4118 Label L0, L1, L2, L3, L4;
4119 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4120 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4121 Register x = rd;
4122 Register y = temps.Acquire();
4123 Register n = temps.Acquire();
4124 DCHECK(xx != y && xx != n);
4125 Move(x, xx);
4126 li(n, Operand(32));
4127#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4128 srliw(y, x, 16);
4129 BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4130 Move(x, y);
4131 addiw(n, n, -16);
4132 bind(&L0);
4133 srliw(y, x, 8);
4134 BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4135 addiw(n, n, -8);
4136 Move(x, y);
4137 bind(&L1);
4138 srliw(y, x, 4);
4139 BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4140 addiw(n, n, -4);
4141 Move(x, y);
4142 bind(&L2);
4143 srliw(y, x, 2);
4144 BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4145 addiw(n, n, -2);
4146 Move(x, y);
4147 bind(&L3);
4148 srliw(y, x, 1);
4149 subw(rd, n, x);
4150 BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4151 addiw(rd, n, -2);
4152 bind(&L4);
4153#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
4154 srli(y, x, 16);
4155 BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4156 Move(x, y);
4157 addi(n, n, -16);
4158 bind(&L0);
4159 srli(y, x, 8);
4160 BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4161 addi(n, n, -8);
4162 Move(x, y);
4163 bind(&L1);
4164 srli(y, x, 4);
4165 BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4166 addi(n, n, -4);
4167 Move(x, y);
4168 bind(&L2);
4169 srli(y, x, 2);
4170 BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4171 addi(n, n, -2);
4172 Move(x, y);
4173 bind(&L3);
4174 srli(y, x, 1);
4175 sub(rd, n, x);
4176 BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4177 addi(rd, n, -2);
4178 bind(&L4);
4179#endif
4180 }
4181}
4182
4183#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4184void MacroAssembler::Clz64(Register rd, Register xx) {
4185 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4186 clz(rd, xx);
4187 } else {
4188 // 64 bit: count number of leading zeros.
4189 // int n = 64;
4190 // unsigned y;
4191
4192 // y = x >>32; if (y != 0) { n = n - 32; x = y; }
4193 // y = x >>16; if (y != 0) { n = n - 16; x = y; }
4194 // y = x >> 8; if (y != 0) { n = n - 8; x = y; }
4195 // y = x >> 4; if (y != 0) { n = n - 4; x = y; }
4196 // y = x >> 2; if (y != 0) { n = n - 2; x = y; }
4197 // y = x >> 1; if (y != 0) {rd = n - 2; return;}
4198 // rd = n - x;
4199
4200 Label L0, L1, L2, L3, L4, L5;
4201 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4202 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4203 Register x = rd;
4204 Register y = temps.Acquire();
4205 Register n = temps.Acquire();
4206 DCHECK(xx != y && xx != n);
4207 Move(x, xx);
4208 li(n, Operand(64));
4209 srli(y, x, 32);
4210 BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4211 addiw(n, n, -32);
4212 Move(x, y);
4213 bind(&L0);
4214 srli(y, x, 16);
4215 BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4216 addiw(n, n, -16);
4217 Move(x, y);
4218 bind(&L1);
4219 srli(y, x, 8);
4220 BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4221 addiw(n, n, -8);
4222 Move(x, y);
4223 bind(&L2);
4224 srli(y, x, 4);
4225 BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4226 addiw(n, n, -4);
4227 Move(x, y);
4228 bind(&L3);
4229 srli(y, x, 2);
4230 BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4231 addiw(n, n, -2);
4232 Move(x, y);
4233 bind(&L4);
4234 srli(y, x, 1);
4235 subw(rd, n, x);
4236 BranchShort(&L5, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4237 addiw(rd, n, -2);
4238 bind(&L5);
4239 }
4240}
4241#endif
4242void MacroAssembler::Ctz32(Register rd, Register rs) {
4243 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4244#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4245 ctzw(rd, rs);
4246#else
4247 ctz(rd, rs);
4248#endif
4249 } else {
4250 // Convert trailing zeroes to trailing ones, and bits to their left
4251 // to zeroes.
4252
4253 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4254 {
4255 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4256 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4257 AddWord(scratch, rs, -1);
4258 Xor(rd, scratch, rs);
4259 And(rd, rd, scratch);
4260 // Count number of leading zeroes.
4261 }
4262 Clz32(rd, rd);
4263 {
4264 // Subtract number of leading zeroes from 32 to get number of trailing
4265 // ones. Remember that the trailing ones were formerly trailing zeroes.
4266 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4267 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4268 li(scratch, 32);
4269 Sub32(rd, scratch, rd);
4270 }
4271 }
4272}
4273#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4274void MacroAssembler::Ctz64(Register rd, Register rs) {
4275 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4276 ctz(rd, rs);
4277 } else {
4278 // Convert trailing zeroes to trailing ones, and bits to their left
4279 // to zeroes.
4280 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4281 {
4282 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4283 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4284 AddWord(scratch, rs, -1);
4285 Xor(rd, scratch, rs);
4286 And(rd, rd, scratch);
4287 // Count number of leading zeroes.
4288 }
4289 Clz64(rd, rd);
4290 {
4291 // Subtract number of leading zeroes from 64 to get number of trailing
4292 // ones. Remember that the trailing ones were formerly trailing zeroes.
4293 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4294 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4295 li(scratch, 64);
4296 SubWord(rd, scratch, rd);
4297 }
4298 }
4299}
4300#endif
4301void MacroAssembler::Popcnt32(Register rd, Register rs, Register scratch) {
4302 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4303#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4304 cpopw(rd, rs);
4305#else
4306 cpop(rd, rs);
4307#endif
4308 } else {
4309 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
4310 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
4311 // https://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#CountBitsSetParallel
4312 //
4313 // A generalization of the best bit counting method to integers of
4314 // bit-widths up to 128 (parameterized by type T) is this:
4315 //
4316 // v = v - ((v >> 1) & (T)~(T)0/3); // temp
4317 // v = (v & (T)~(T)0/15*3) + ((v >> 2) & (T)~(T)0/15*3); // temp
4318 // v = (v + (v >> 4)) & (T)~(T)0/255*15; // temp
4319 // c = (T)(v * ((T)~(T)0/255)) >> (sizeof(T) - 1) * BITS_PER_BYTE; //count
4320 //
4321 // There are algorithms which are faster in the cases where very few
4322 // bits are set but the algorithm here attempts to minimize the total
4323 // number of instructions executed even when a large number of bits
4324 // are set.
4325 // The number of instruction is 20.
4326 // uint32_t B0 = 0x55555555; // (T)~(T)0/3
4327 // uint32_t B1 = 0x33333333; // (T)~(T)0/15*3
4328 // uint32_t B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F; // (T)~(T)0/255*15
4329 // uint32_t value = 0x01010101; // (T)~(T)0/255
4330
4331 uint32_t shift = 24;
4332 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4333 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4334 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4335 Register value = temps.Acquire();
4336 DCHECK((rd != value) && (rs != value));
4337 li(value, 0x01010101); // value = 0x01010101;
4338 li(scratch2, 0x55555555); // B0 = 0x55555555;
4339 Srl32(scratch, rs, 1);
4340 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4341 Sub32(scratch, rs, scratch);
4342 li(scratch2, 0x33333333); // B1 = 0x33333333;
4343 slli(rd, scratch2, 4);
4344 or_(scratch2, scratch2, rd);
4345 And(rd, scratch, scratch2);
4346 Srl32(scratch, scratch, 2);
4347 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4348 Add32(scratch, rd, scratch);
4349 Srl32(rd, scratch, 4);
4350 Add32(rd, rd, scratch);
4351 li(scratch2, 0xF);
4352 Mul32(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F;
4353 And(rd, rd, scratch2);
4354 Mul32(rd, rd, value);
4355 Srl32(rd, rd, shift);
4356 }
4357}
4358
4359#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4360void MacroAssembler::Popcnt64(Register rd, Register rs, Register scratch) {
4361 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4362 cpop(rd, rs);
4363 } else {
4364 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
4365 DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
4366 // uint64_t B0 = 0x5555555555555555l; // (T)~(T)0/3
4367 // uint64_t B1 = 0x3333333333333333l; // (T)~(T)0/15*3
4368 // uint64_t B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fl; // (T)~(T)0/255*15
4369 // uint64_t value = 0x0101010101010101l; // (T)~(T)0/255
4370 // uint64_t shift = 24; // (sizeof(T) - 1) * BITS_PER_BYTE
4371 uint64_t shift = 24;
4372 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4373 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4374 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4375 Register value = temps.Acquire();
4376 DCHECK((rd != value) && (rs != value));
4377 li(value, 0x1111111111111111l); // value = 0x1111111111111111l;
4378 li(scratch2, 5);
4379 Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B0 = 0x5555555555555555l;
4380 Srl64(scratch, rs, 1);
4381 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4382 SubWord(scratch, rs, scratch);
4383 li(scratch2, 3);
4384 Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B1 = 0x3333333333333333l;
4385 And(rd, scratch, scratch2);
4386 Srl64(scratch, scratch, 2);
4387 And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4388 AddWord(scratch, rd, scratch);
4389 Srl64(rd, scratch, 4);
4390 AddWord(rd, rd, scratch);
4391 li(scratch2, 0xF);
4392 li(value, 0x0101010101010101l); // value = 0x0101010101010101l;
4393 Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fl;
4394 And(rd, rd, scratch2);
4395 Mul64(rd, rd, value);
4396 srli(rd, rd, 32 + shift);
4397 }
4398}
4399#endif
4400void MacroAssembler::TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(Register result,
4401 DoubleRegister double_input,
4402 Label* done) {
4403 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4404 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4405 // if scratch == 1, exception happens during truncation
4406 Trunc_w_d(result, double_input, scratch);
4407 // If we had no exceptions (i.e., scratch==1) we are done.
4408 Branch(done, eq, scratch, Operand(1));
4409}
4410
4411void MacroAssembler::TruncateDoubleToI(Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone,
4412 Register result,
4413 DoubleRegister double_input,
4414 StubCallMode stub_mode) {
4415 Label done;
4416
4417 TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(result, double_input, &done);
4418
4419 // If we fell through then inline version didn't succeed - call stub
4420 // instead.
4421 push(ra);
4422 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize)); // Put input on stack.
4423 fsd(double_input, sp, 0);
4424#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4425 if (stub_mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
4426 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kDoubleToI), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
4427#else
4428 // For balance.
4429 if (false) {
4430#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4431 } else {
4432 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kDoubleToI);
4433 }
4434 LoadWord(result, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4435
4436 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize));
4437 pop(ra);
4438
4439 bind(&done);
4440}
4441
4442// BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK checks that conditional jump arguments are correct.
4443#define BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt) \
4444 DCHECK((cond == cc_always && rs == zero_reg && rt.rm() == zero_reg) || \
4445 (cond != cc_always && (rs != zero_reg || rt.rm() != zero_reg)))
4446
4447void MacroAssembler::Branch(int32_t offset) {
4448 DCHECK(is_int21(offset));
4449 BranchShort(offset);
4450}
4451
4452void MacroAssembler::Branch(int32_t offset, Condition cond, Register rs,
4453 const Operand& rt, Label::Distance distance) {
4454 bool is_near = BranchShortCheck(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4455 DCHECK(is_near);
4456 USE(is_near);
4457}
4458
4459void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L) {
4460 if (L->is_bound()) {
4461 if (is_near(L)) {
4462 BranchShort(L);
4463 } else {
4464 BranchLong(L);
4465 }
4466 } else {
4467 if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4468 BranchLong(L);
4469 } else {
4470 BranchShort(L);
4471 }
4472 }
4473}
4474
4475void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4476 const Operand& rt, Label::Distance distance) {
4477 if (L->is_bound()) {
4478 if (!BranchShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt)) {
4479 if (cond != cc_always) {
4480 Label skip;
4481 Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4482 BlockPoolsScope block_pools(this, 3 * kInstrSize);
4483 BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4484 BranchLong(L);
4485 bind(&skip);
4486 } else {
4487 BranchLong(L);
4488 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4489 }
4490 }
4491 } else {
4492 DEBUG_PRINTF("\t Branch is_trampoline_emitted %d\n",
4493 is_trampoline_emitted());
4494 if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4495 if (cond != cc_always) {
4496 Label skip;
4497 Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4498 BlockPoolsScope block_pools(this, 3 * kInstrSize);
4499 BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4500 BranchLong(L);
4501 bind(&skip);
4502 } else {
4503 BranchLong(L);
4504 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4505 }
4506 } else {
4507 BranchShort(L, cond, rs, rt);
4508 }
4509 }
4510}
4511
4512void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4513 RootIndex index, Label::Distance distance) {
4514 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4515 Register right = temps.Acquire();
4516 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4517 Register left = rs;
4518 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
4519 is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
4520 left = temps.Acquire();
4521 Sll32(left, rs, 0);
4522 }
4523 LoadTaggedRoot(right, index);
4524 Branch(L, cond, left, Operand(right));
4525 } else {
4526 LoadRoot(right, index);
4527 Branch(L, cond, rs, Operand(right));
4528 }
4529}
4530
4531void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedAndBranch(Label* label, Condition cond,
4532 Register r1, const Operand& r2,
4533 bool need_link) {
4534 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4535 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4536 Register scratch0 = temps.Acquire();
4537 Sll32(scratch0, r1, 0);
4538 if (IsZero(r2)) {
4539 Branch(label, cond, scratch0, Operand(zero_reg));
4540 } else {
4541 Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
4542 if (r2.is_reg()) {
4543 Sll32(scratch1, r2.rm(), 0);
4544 } else {
4545 li(scratch1, r2);
4546 Sll32(scratch1, scratch1, 0);
4547 }
4548 Branch(label, cond, scratch0, Operand(scratch1));
4549 }
4550 } else {
4551 Branch(label, cond, r1, r2);
4552 }
4553}
4554
4555void MacroAssembler::BranchShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L) {
4556 DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4557 offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4558 j(offset);
4559}
4560
4561void MacroAssembler::BranchShort(int32_t offset) {
4562 DCHECK(is_int21(offset));
4563 BranchShortHelper(offset, nullptr);
4564}
4565
4566void MacroAssembler::BranchShort(Label* L) { BranchShortHelper(0, L); }
4567
4568int32_t MacroAssembler::GetOffset(int32_t offset, Label* L, OffsetSize bits) {
4569 if (L) {
4570 offset = branch_offset_helper(L, bits);
4571 } else {
4572 DCHECK(is_intn(offset, bits));
4573 }
4574 return offset;
4575}
4576
4577Register MacroAssembler::GetRtAsRegisterHelper(const Operand& rt,
4578 Register scratch) {
4579 Register r2 = no_reg;
4580 if (rt.is_reg()) {
4581 r2 = rt.rm();
4582 } else {
4583 r2 = scratch;
4584 li(r2, rt);
4585 }
4586
4587 return r2;
4588}
4589
4590bool MacroAssembler::CalculateOffset(Label* L, int32_t* offset,
4591 OffsetSize bits) {
4592 if (!is_near(L, bits)) return false;
4593 *offset = GetOffset(*offset, L, bits);
4594 return true;
4595}
4596
4597bool MacroAssembler::CalculateOffset(Label* L, int32_t* offset, OffsetSize bits,
4598 Register* scratch, const Operand& rt) {
4599 if (!is_near(L, bits)) return false;
4600 *scratch = GetRtAsRegisterHelper(rt, *scratch);
4601 *offset = GetOffset(*offset, L, bits);
4602 return true;
4603}
4604
4605bool MacroAssembler::BranchShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L, Condition cond,
4606 Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4607 DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4608 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4609 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4610 Register scratch = no_reg;
4611 if (!rt.is_reg()) {
4612 if (rt.immediate() == 0) {
4613 scratch = zero_reg;
4614 } else {
4615 scratch = temps.Acquire();
4616 li(scratch, rt);
4617 }
4618 } else {
4619 scratch = rt.rm();
4620 }
4621 {
4622 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4623 switch (cond) {
4624 case cc_always:
4625 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4626 j(offset);
4627 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4628 break;
4629 case eq:
4630 // rs == rt
4631 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4632 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4633 j(offset);
4634 } else {
4635 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4636 beq(rs, scratch, offset);
4637 }
4638 break;
4639 case ne:
4640 // rs != rt
4641 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4642 break; // No code needs to be emitted
4643 } else {
4644 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4645 bne(rs, scratch, offset);
4646 }
4647 break;
4648
4649 // Signed comparison.
4650 case greater:
4651 // rs > rt
4652 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4653 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4654 } else {
4655 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4656 bgt(rs, scratch, offset);
4657 }
4658 break;
4659 case greater_equal:
4660 // rs >= rt
4661 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4662 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4663 j(offset);
4664 } else {
4665 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4666 bge(rs, scratch, offset);
4667 }
4668 break;
4669 case less:
4670 // rs < rt
4671 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4672 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4673 } else {
4674 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4675 blt(rs, scratch, offset);
4676 }
4677 break;
4678 case less_equal:
4679 // rs <= rt
4680 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4681 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4682 j(offset);
4683 } else {
4684 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4685 ble(rs, scratch, offset);
4686 }
4687 break;
4688
4689 // Unsigned comparison.
4690 case Ugreater:
4691 // rs > rt
4692 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4693 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4694 } else {
4695 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4696 bgtu(rs, scratch, offset);
4697 }
4698 break;
4699 case Ugreater_equal:
4700 // rs >= rt
4701 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4702 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4703 j(offset);
4704 } else {
4705 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4706 bgeu(rs, scratch, offset);
4707 }
4708 break;
4709 case Uless:
4710 // rs < rt
4711 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4712 break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4713 } else {
4714 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4715 bltu(rs, scratch, offset);
4716 }
4717 break;
4718 case Uless_equal:
4719 // rs <= rt
4720 if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4721 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4722 j(offset);
4723 } else {
4724 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4725 bleu(rs, scratch, offset);
4726 }
4727 break;
4728 case Condition::overflow:
4729 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4730 bnez(rs, offset);
4731 break;
4732 case Condition::no_overflow:
4733 if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4734 beqz(rs, offset);
4735 break;
4736 default:
4737 UNREACHABLE();
4738 }
4739 }
4740
4741 CheckTrampolinePoolQuick(1);
4742 return true;
4743}
4744
4745bool MacroAssembler::BranchShortCheck(int32_t offset, Label* L, Condition cond,
4746 Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4747 BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4748
4749 if (!L) {
4750 DCHECK(is_int13(offset));
4751 return BranchShortHelper(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4752 } else {
4753 DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
4754 return BranchShortHelper(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4755 }
4756}
4757
4758void MacroAssembler::BranchShort(int32_t offset, Condition cond, Register rs,
4759 const Operand& rt) {
4760 BranchShortCheck(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4761}
4762
4763void MacroAssembler::BranchShort(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4764 const Operand& rt) {
4765 BranchShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4766}
4767
4768void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLink(int32_t offset) {
4769 BranchAndLinkShort(offset);
4770}
4771
4772void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLink(int32_t offset, Condition cond, Register rs,
4773 const Operand& rt) {
4774 bool is_near = BranchAndLinkShortCheck(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4775 DCHECK(is_near);
4776 USE(is_near);
4777}
4778
4779void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLink(Label* L) {
4780 if (L->is_bound()) {
4781 if (is_near(L)) {
4782 BranchAndLinkShort(L);
4783 } else {
4784 BranchAndLinkLong(L);
4785 }
4786 } else {
4787 if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4788 BranchAndLinkLong(L);
4789 } else {
4790 BranchAndLinkShort(L);
4791 }
4792 }
4793}
4794
4795void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLink(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4796 const Operand& rt) {
4797 if (L->is_bound()) {
4798 if (!BranchAndLinkShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt)) {
4799 Label skip;
4800 Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4801 BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4802 BranchAndLinkLong(L);
4803 bind(&skip);
4804 }
4805 } else {
4806 if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4807 Label skip;
4808 Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4809 BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4810 BranchAndLinkLong(L);
4811 bind(&skip);
4812 } else {
4813 BranchAndLinkShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4814 }
4815 }
4816}
4817
4818void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L) {
4819 DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4820 offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4821 jal(offset);
4822}
4823
4824void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShort(int32_t offset) {
4825 DCHECK(is_int21(offset));
4826 BranchAndLinkShortHelper(offset, nullptr);
4827}
4828
4829void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShort(Label* L) {
4830 BranchAndLinkShortHelper(0, L);
4831}
4832
4833// Pre r6 we need to use a bgezal or bltzal, but they can't be used directly
4834// with the slt instructions. We could use sub or add instead but we would miss
4835// overflow cases, so we keep slt and add an intermediate third instruction.
4836bool MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L,
4837 Condition cond, Register rs,
4838 const Operand& rt) {
4839 DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4840 if (!is_near(L, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4841
4842 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4843 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4844 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4845
4846 if (cond == cc_always) {
4847 offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4848 jal(offset);
4849 } else {
4850 Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs,
4851 Operand(GetRtAsRegisterHelper(rt, scratch)));
4852 offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4853 jal(offset);
4854 }
4855
4856 return true;
4857}
4858
4859bool MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShortCheck(int32_t offset, Label* L,
4860 Condition cond, Register rs,
4861 const Operand& rt) {
4862 BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4863
4864 if (!L) {
4865 DCHECK(is_int21(offset));
4866 return BranchAndLinkShortHelper(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4867 } else {
4868 DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
4869 return BranchAndLinkShortHelper(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4870 }
4871}
4872
4873void MacroAssembler::LoadFromConstantsTable(Register destination,
4874 int constant_index) {
4875 DCHECK(RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(RootIndex::kBuiltinsConstantsTable));
4876 LoadRoot(destination, RootIndex::kBuiltinsConstantsTable);
4877 LoadTaggedField(destination,
4878 FieldMemOperand(destination, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(
4879 constant_index)));
4880}
4881
4882void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRelative(Register destination, int32_t offset) {
4883 LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
4884}
4885
4886void MacroAssembler::StoreRootRelative(int32_t offset, Register value) {
4887 StoreWord(value, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
4888}
4889
4890MemOperand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4891 ExternalReference reference, Register scratch) {
4892 if (root_array_available()) {
4893 if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
4894 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, reference.offset_from_root_register());
4895 }
4896 if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
4897 int64_t offset =
4898 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4899 if (is_int32(offset)) {
4900 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4901 }
4902 }
4903 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
4904 if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
4905 // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
4906 // kRootRegister.
4907 intptr_t offset =
4908 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4909 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
4910 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4911 } else {
4912 // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
4913 DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4914 LoadWord(scratch,
4915 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4916 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
4917 isolate(), reference)));
4918 return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4919 }
4920 }
4921 }
4922 DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4923 li(scratch, reference);
4924 return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4925}
4926
4927void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRegisterOffset(Register destination,
4928 intptr_t offset) {
4929 if (offset == 0) {
4930 Move(destination, kRootRegister);
4931 } else {
4932 AddWord(destination, kRootRegister, Operand(offset));
4933 }
4934}
4935
4936void MacroAssembler::Jump(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
4937 const Operand& rt) {
4938 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4939 if (cond == cc_always) {
4940 jr(target);
4941 ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
4942 } else {
4943 BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4944 Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4945 jr(target);
4946 }
4947}
4948
4949void MacroAssembler::Jump(intptr_t target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
4950 Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4951 Label skip;
4952 if (cond != cc_always) {
4953 Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4954 }
4955 {
4956 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4957 li(t6, Operand(target, rmode));
4958 Jump(t6, al, zero_reg, Operand(zero_reg));
4959 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4960 bind(&skip);
4961 }
4962}
4963
4964void MacroAssembler::Jump(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode, Condition cond,
4965 Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4966 DCHECK(!RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4967 Jump(static_cast<intptr_t>(target), rmode, cond, rs, rt);
4968}
4969
4970void MacroAssembler::Jump(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
4971 Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4972 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4973 DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
4974 Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
4975
4976 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
4977 if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
4978 // Inline the trampoline.
4979 Label skip;
4980 if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4981 TailCallBuiltin(builtin);
4982 bind(&skip);
4983 return;
4984 }
4985 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
4986 if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
4987 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
4988 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
4989 Label skip;
4990 if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4991 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
4992 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4993 GenPCRelativeJump(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
4994 bind(&skip);
4995 } else {
4996 Jump(code.address(), rmode, cond);
4997 }
4998}
4999
5000void MacroAssembler::Jump(const ExternalReference& reference) {
5001 li(t6, reference);
5002 Jump(t6);
5003}
5004
5005// Note: To call gcc-compiled C code on riscv64, you must call through t6.
5006void MacroAssembler::Call(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
5007 const Operand& rt) {
5008 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5009 if (cond == cc_always) {
5010 jalr(ra, target, 0);
5011 } else {
5012 BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
5013 Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5014 jalr(ra, target, 0);
5015 }
5016}
5017
5018void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRootAndBranch(const Register& obj,
5019 RootIndex index, Condition cc,
5020 Label* target) {
5021 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5022 AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(obj);
5023 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5024 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index)) {
5025 CompareTaggedAndBranch(target, cc, obj, Operand(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index)));
5026 return;
5027 }
5028 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5029 DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5030 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
5031 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
5032 DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
5033 LoadRoot(temp, index);
5034 CompareTaggedAndBranch(target, cc, obj, Operand(temp));
5035}
5036// Compare the object in a register to a value from the root list.
5037void MacroAssembler::CompareRootAndBranch(const Register& obj, RootIndex index,
5038 Condition cc, Label* target,
5039 ComparisonMode mode) {
5040 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5041 if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
5042 !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5043 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
5044 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5045 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5046 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
5047 DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
5048 LoadRoot(temp, index);
5049 Branch(target, cc, obj, Operand(temp));
5050 return;
5051 }
5052 CompareTaggedRootAndBranch(obj, index, cc, target);
5053}
5054#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5055// Compare the tagged object in a register to a value from the root list
5056// and put 0 into result if equal or 1 otherwise.
5057void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRoot(const Register& with, RootIndex index,
5058 const Register& result) {
5059 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5060 AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(with);
5061 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index)) {
5062 Li(result, ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
5063 MacroAssembler::CmpTagged(result, with, result);
5064 return;
5065 }
5066 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5067 DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5068 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
5069 LoadRoot(result, index);
5070 MacroAssembler::CmpTagged(result, with, result);
5071}
5072
5073void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(const Register& obj, RootIndex index,
5074 const Register& result, ComparisonMode mode) {
5075 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5076 if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
5077 !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5078 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
5079 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5080 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5081 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
5082 DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
5083 LoadRoot(temp, index);
5084 CompareI(result, obj, Operand(temp),
5085 Condition::ne); // result is 0 if equal or 1 otherwise
5086 return;
5087 }
5088 // FIXME: check that 0/1 in result is expected for all CompareRoot callers
5089 CompareTaggedRoot(obj, index, result);
5090}
5091#endif
5092
5093void MacroAssembler::JumpIfIsInRange(Register value, unsigned lower_limit,
5094 unsigned higher_limit,
5095 Label* on_in_range) {
5096 if (lower_limit != 0) {
5097 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5098 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5099 SubWord(scratch, value, Operand(lower_limit));
5100 Branch(on_in_range, Uless_equal, scratch,
5101 Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
5102 } else {
5103 Branch(on_in_range, Uless_equal, value,
5104 Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
5105 }
5106}
5107
5108// The calculated offset is either:
5109// * the 'target' input unmodified if this is a Wasm call, or
5110// * the offset of the target from the current PC, in instructions, for any
5111// other type of call.
5112int64_t MacroAssembler::CalculateTargetOffset(Address target,
5113 RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
5114 uint8_t* pc) {
5115 int64_t offset = static_cast<int64_t>(target);
5116 if (rmode == RelocInfo::WASM_CALL || rmode == RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL) {
5117 // The target of WebAssembly calls is still an index instead of an actual
5118 // address at this point, and needs to be encoded as-is.
5119 return offset;
5120 }
5121 offset -= reinterpret_cast<int64_t>(pc);
5122 DCHECK_EQ(offset % kInstrSize, 0);
5123 return offset;
5124}
5125
5126void MacroAssembler::Call(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode, Condition cond,
5127 Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5128 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5129 if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
5130 int64_t offset = CalculateTargetOffset(target, rmode, pc_);
5131 DCHECK(is_int32(offset));
5132 near_call(static_cast<int>(offset), rmode);
5133 } else {
5134 li(t6, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(target), rmode), ADDRESS_LOAD);
5135 Call(t6, cond, rs, rt);
5136 }
5137}
5138
5139void MacroAssembler::Call(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
5140 Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5141 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5142 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5143 DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
5144 Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
5145
5146 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
5147 if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
5148 // Inline the trampoline.
5149 CHECK_EQ(cond, Condition::al); // Implement if necessary.
5150 CallBuiltin(builtin);
5151 return;
5152 }
5153
5154 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5155
5156 if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
5157 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5158 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5159 Label skip;
5160 if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5161 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5162 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5163 GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5164 bind(&skip);
5165 } else {
5166 Call(code.address(), rmode);
5167 }
5168}
5169
5170void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(Register builtin_index,
5171 Register target) {
5172#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5173 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 8);
5174#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5175 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 4);
5176#endif
5177 static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1);
5178 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5179
5180 // The builtin register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
5181 SmiUntag(target, builtin_index);
5182 CalcScaledAddress(target, kRootRegister, target, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5183 LoadWord(target,
5184 MemOperand(target, IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset()));
5185}
5186
5187void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltinByIndex(Register builtin_index,
5188 Register target) {
5189 LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(builtin_index, target);
5190 Call(target);
5191}
5192
5193void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
5194 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
5195 switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
5196 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
5197 li(t6, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
5198 Call(t6);
5199 break;
5200 }
5201 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
5202 near_call(static_cast<int>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
5203 break;
5204 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
5205 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5206 Call(t6);
5207 break;
5208 }
5209 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
5210 if (options().use_pc_relative_calls_and_jumps_for_mksnapshot) {
5211 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
5212 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5213 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5214 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5215 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5216 GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5217 } else {
5218 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5219 Call(t6);
5220 }
5221 break;
5222 }
5223 }
5224}
5225
5226void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, Condition cond,
5227 Register type, Operand range) {
5228 Label done;
5229 Branch(&done, NegateCondition(cond), type, range);
5230 TailCallBuiltin(builtin);
5231 bind(&done);
5232}
5233
5234void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
5235 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this,
5236 CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("tail call", builtin));
5237 switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
5238 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
5239 li(t6, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
5240 Jump(t6);
5241 break;
5242 }
5243 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
5244 near_jump(static_cast<int>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
5245 break;
5246 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
5247 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5248 Jump(t6);
5249 break;
5250 }
5251 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
5252 if (options().use_pc_relative_calls_and_jumps_for_mksnapshot) {
5253 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
5254 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5255 DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5256 RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5257 static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5258 GenPCRelativeJump(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5259 } else {
5260 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5261 Jump(t6);
5262 }
5263 break;
5264 }
5265 }
5266}
5267
5268void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin builtin,
5269 Register destination) {
5270 LoadWord(destination, EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
5271}
5272
5273MemOperand MacroAssembler::EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(Builtin builtin) {
5274 DCHECK(root_array_available());
5275 return MemOperand(kRootRegister,
5276 IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(builtin));
5277}
5278
5279void MacroAssembler::PatchAndJump(Address target) {
5280 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5281 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5282 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5283 auipc(scratch, 0); // Load PC into scratch
5284 LoadWord(t6, MemOperand(scratch, kInstrSize * 4));
5285 jr(t6);
5286 nop(); // For alignment
5287#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5288 DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(pc_) % 8, 0);
5289#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5290 DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint32_t>(pc_) % 4, 0);
5291#endif
5292 *reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(pc_) = target; // pc_ should be align.
5293 pc_ += sizeof(uintptr_t);
5294}
5295
5296void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
5297 // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
5298 // once an exit frame has been constructed.
5299 //
5300 // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
5301 // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
5302 // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
5303 //
5304 // Compute the return address in lr to return to after the jump below. The
5305 // pc is already at '+ 8' from the current instruction; but return is after
5306 // three instructions, so add another 4 to pc to get the return address.
5307 //
5308 Assembler::BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5309 int kNumInstructionsToJump = 5;
5310 if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension) kNumInstructionsToJump = 4;
5311 Label find_ra;
5312 // Adjust the value in ra to point to the correct return location, one
5313 // instruction past the real call into C code (the jalr(t6)), and push it.
5314 // This is the return address of the exit frame.
5315 auipc(ra, 0); // Set ra the current PC
5316 bind(&find_ra);
5317 addi(ra, ra,
5318 (kNumInstructionsToJump + 1) *
5319 kInstrSize); // Set ra to insn after the call
5320
5321 // This spot was reserved in EnterExitFrame.
5322 StoreWord(ra, MemOperand(sp));
5323 addi(sp, sp, -kCArgsSlotsSize);
5324 // Stack is still aligned.
5325
5326 // Call the C routine.
5327 Mv(t6,
5328 target); // Function pointer to t6 to conform to ABI for PIC.
5329 jalr(t6);
5330 // Make sure the stored 'ra' points to this position.
5331 DCHECK_EQ(kNumInstructionsToJump, InstructionsGeneratedSince(&find_ra));
5332}
5333
5334void MacroAssembler::Ret(Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5335 Jump(ra, cond, rs, rt);
5336 if (cond == al) {
5337 ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
5338 }
5339}
5340
5341void MacroAssembler::BranchLong(Label* L) {
5342 // Generate position independent long branch.
5343 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5344 int32_t imm;
5345 imm = branch_long_offset(L);
5346 if (L->is_bound() && is_intn(imm, Assembler::kJumpOffsetBits) &&
5347 (imm & 1) == 0) {
5348 j(imm);
5349 nop();
5350 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
5351 return;
5352 }
5353 GenPCRelativeJump(t6, imm);
5354 EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
5355}
5356
5357void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkLong(Label* L) {
5358 // Generate position independent long branch and link.
5359 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5360 int32_t imm;
5361 imm = branch_long_offset(L);
5362 if (L->is_bound() && is_intn(imm, Assembler::kJumpOffsetBits) &&
5363 (imm & 1) == 0) {
5364 jal(t6, imm);
5365 nop();
5366 return;
5367 }
5368 GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, imm);
5369}
5370
5371void MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(int drop) {
5372 AddWord(sp, sp, drop * kSystemPointerSize);
5373 Ret();
5374}
5375
5376void MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(int drop, Condition cond, Register r1,
5377 const Operand& r2) {
5378 // Both Drop and Ret need to be conditional.
5379 Label skip;
5380 if (cond != cc_always) {
5381 Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), r1, r2);
5382 }
5383
5384 Drop(drop);
5385 Ret();
5386
5387 if (cond != cc_always) {
5388 bind(&skip);
5389 }
5390}
5391
5392void MacroAssembler::Drop(int count, Condition cond, Register reg,
5393 const Operand& op) {
5394 if (count <= 0) {
5395 return;
5396 }
5397
5398 Label skip;
5399
5400 if (cond != al) {
5401 Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), reg, op);
5402 }
5403
5404 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(count * kSystemPointerSize));
5405
5406 if (cond != al) {
5407 bind(&skip);
5408 }
5409}
5410
5411void MacroAssembler::Swap(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register scratch) {
5412 if (scratch == no_reg) {
5413 Xor(reg1, reg1, Operand(reg2));
5414 Xor(reg2, reg2, Operand(reg1));
5415 Xor(reg1, reg1, Operand(reg2));
5416 } else {
5417 Mv(scratch, reg1);
5418 Mv(reg1, reg2);
5419 Mv(reg2, scratch);
5420 }
5421}
5422
5423void MacroAssembler::Call(Label* target) { BranchAndLink(target); }
5424
5425void MacroAssembler::LoadAddress(Register dst, Label* target,
5426 RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
5427 int32_t offset;
5428 if (CalculateOffset(target, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset32)) {
5429 CHECK(is_int32(offset + 0x800));
5430 int32_t Hi20 = (((int32_t)offset + 0x800) >> 12);
5431 int32_t Lo12 = (int32_t)offset << 20 >> 20;
5432 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5433 auipc(dst, Hi20);
5434 addi(dst, dst, Lo12);
5435 } else {
5436 uintptr_t address = jump_address(target);
5437 li(dst, Operand(address, rmode), ADDRESS_LOAD);
5438 }
5439}
5440
5441void MacroAssembler::Switch(Register scratch, Register value,
5442 int case_value_base, Label** labels,
5443 int num_labels) {
5444 Register table = scratch;
5445 Label fallthrough, jump_table;
5446 if (case_value_base != 0) {
5447 SubWord(value, value, Operand(case_value_base));
5448 }
5449 Branch(&fallthrough, Condition::Ugreater_equal, value, Operand(num_labels));
5450 LoadAddress(table, &jump_table);
5451 CalcScaledAddress(table, table, value, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5452 LoadWord(table, MemOperand(table, 0));
5453 Jump(table);
5454 // Calculate label area size and let MASM know that it will be impossible to
5455 // create the trampoline within the range. That forces MASM to create the
5456 // trampoline right here if necessary, i.e. if label area is too large and
5457 // all unbound forward branches cannot be bound over it. Use nop() because the
5458 // trampoline cannot be emitted right after Jump().
5459 nop();
5460 static constexpr int mask = kInstrSize - 1;
5461 int aligned_label_area_size = num_labels * kUIntptrSize + kSystemPointerSize;
5462 int instructions_per_label_area =
5463 ((aligned_label_area_size + mask) & ~mask) >> kInstrSizeLog2;
5464 BlockTrampolinePoolFor(instructions_per_label_area);
5465 // Emit the jump table inline, under the assumption that it's not too big.
5466 Align(kSystemPointerSize);
5467 bind(&jump_table);
5468 for (int i = 0; i < num_labels; ++i) {
5469 dd(labels[i]);
5470 }
5471 bind(&fallthrough);
5472}
5473
5474void MacroAssembler::Push(Tagged<Smi> smi) {
5475 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5476 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5477 li(scratch, Operand(smi));
5478 push(scratch);
5479}
5480
5481void MacroAssembler::Push(Tagged<TaggedIndex> index) {
5482 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5483 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5484 li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<uint32_t>(index.ptr())));
5485 push(scratch);
5486}
5487
5488void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size,
5489 PushArrayOrder order) {
5490 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5491 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5492 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5493 Label loop, entry;
5494 if (order == PushArrayOrder::kReverse) {
5495 Mv(scratch, zero_reg);
5496 jmp(&entry);
5497 bind(&loop);
5498 CalcScaledAddress(scratch2, array, scratch, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5499 LoadWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
5500 push(scratch2);
5501 AddWord(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
5502 bind(&entry);
5503 Branch(&loop, less, scratch, Operand(size));
5504 } else {
5505 Mv(scratch, size);
5506 jmp(&entry);
5507 bind(&loop);
5508 CalcScaledAddress(scratch2, array, scratch, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5509 LoadWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
5510 push(scratch2);
5511 bind(&entry);
5512 AddWord(scratch, scratch, Operand(-1));
5513 Branch(&loop, greater_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5514 }
5515}
5516
5517void MacroAssembler::Push(Handle<HeapObject> handle) {
5518 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5519 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5520 li(scratch, Operand(handle));
5521 push(scratch);
5522}
5523
5524// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
5525// Exception handling.
5526
5527void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
5528 // Adjust this code if not the case.
5529 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
5530 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0 * kSystemPointerSize);
5531
5532 Push(Smi::zero()); // Padding.
5533
5534 // Link the current handler as the next handler.
5535 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5536 Register handler_address = temps.Acquire();
5537 li(handler_address,
5538 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
5539 Register handler = temps.Acquire();
5540 LoadWord(handler, MemOperand(handler_address));
5541 push(handler);
5542
5543 // Set this new handler as the current one.
5544 StoreWord(sp, MemOperand(handler_address));
5545}
5546
5547void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
5548 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
5549 pop(a1);
5550 AddWord(sp, sp,
5551 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(StackHandlerConstants::kSize -
5552 kSystemPointerSize)));
5553 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5554 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5555 li(scratch,
5556 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
5557 StoreWord(a1, MemOperand(scratch));
5558}
5559
5560void MacroAssembler::FPUCanonicalizeNaN(const DoubleRegister dst,
5561 const DoubleRegister src) {
5562 // Subtracting 0.0 preserves all inputs except for signalling NaNs, which
5563 // become quiet NaNs. We use fsub rather than fadd because fsub preserves -0.0
5564 // inputs: -0.0 + 0.0 = 0.0, but -0.0 - 0.0 = -0.0.
5565 if (!IsDoubleZeroRegSet()) {
5566 LoadFPRImmediate(kDoubleRegZero, 0.0);
5567 }
5568 fsub_d(dst, src, kDoubleRegZero);
5569}
5570
5571void MacroAssembler::MovFromFloatResult(const DoubleRegister dst) {
5572 Move(dst, fa0); // Reg fa0 is FP return value.
5573}
5574
5575void MacroAssembler::MovFromFloatParameter(const DoubleRegister dst) {
5576 Move(dst, fa0); // Reg fa0 is FP first argument value.
5577}
5578
5579void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameter(DoubleRegister src) { Move(fa0, src); }
5580
5581void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatResult(DoubleRegister src) { Move(fa0, src); }
5582
5583void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameters(DoubleRegister src1,
5584 DoubleRegister src2) {
5585 const DoubleRegister fparg2 = fa1;
5586 if (src2 == fa0) {
5587 DCHECK(src1 != fparg2);
5588 Move(fparg2, src2);
5589 Move(fa0, src1);
5590 } else {
5591 Move(fa0, src1);
5592 Move(fparg2, src2);
5593 }
5594}

5596// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5597// JavaScript invokes.
5598
5599void MacroAssembler::LoadStackLimit(Register destination, StackLimitKind kind) {
5600 DCHECK(root_array_available());
5601 intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
5602 ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
5603 : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();
5604 LoadWord(destination,
5605 MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset)));
5606}
5607
5608void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(Register num_args, Register scratch1,
5609 Register scratch2,
5610 Label* stack_overflow, Label* done) {
5611 // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
5612 // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
5613 // limit" is checked.
5614 DCHECK(stack_overflow != nullptr || done != nullptr);
5615 LoadStackLimit(scratch1, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
5616 // Make scratch1 the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
5617 // here which will cause scratch1 to become negative.
5618 SubWord(scratch1, sp, scratch1);
5619 // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
5620 SllWord(scratch2, num_args, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5621 // Signed comparison.
5622 if (stack_overflow != nullptr) {
5623 Branch(stack_overflow, le, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
5624 } else if (done != nullptr) {
5625 Branch(done, gt, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
5626 } else {
5627 UNREACHABLE();
5628 }
5629}
5630
5631void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
5632 Register actual_parameter_count,
5633 Label* done, InvokeType type) {
5634 Label regular_invoke;
5635
5636 // a0: actual arguments count
5637 // a1: function (passed through to callee)
5638 // a2: expected arguments count
5639
5640 DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, a0);
5641 DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, a2);
5642
5643 // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
5644 // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
5645 SubWord(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
5646 actual_parameter_count);
5647 Branch(&regular_invoke, le, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5648
5649 Label stack_overflow;
5650 {
5651 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5652 StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, temps.Acquire(),
5653 temps.Acquire(), &stack_overflow);
5654 }
5655 // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
5656 // receiver and the return address.
5657 {
5658 Label copy;
5659 Register src = a6, dest = a7;
5660 Move(src, sp);
5661 SllWord(t0, expected_parameter_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5662 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(t0));
5663 // Update stack pointer.
5664 Move(dest, sp);
5665 Move(t0, actual_parameter_count);
5666 bind(&copy);
5667 LoadWord(t1, MemOperand(src, 0));
5668 StoreWord(t1, MemOperand(dest, 0));
5669 SubWord(t0, t0, Operand(1));
5670 AddWord(src, src, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5671 AddWord(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5672 Branch(&copy, gt, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5673 }
5674
5675 // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
5676 LoadRoot(t0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5677 {
5678 Label loop;
5679 bind(&loop);
5680 StoreWord(t0, MemOperand(a7, 0));
5681 SubWord(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
5682 AddWord(a7, a7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5683 Branch(&loop, gt, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5684 }
5685 Branch(&regular_invoke);
5686
5687 bind(&stack_overflow);
5688 {
5689 FrameScope frame(
5690 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5691 CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
5692 break_(0xCC);
5693 }
5694 bind(&regular_invoke);
5695}
5696
5697void MacroAssembler::CheckDebugHook(Register fun, Register new_target,
5698 Register expected_parameter_count,
5699 Register actual_parameter_count) {
5700 Label skip_hook;
5701 {
5702 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5703 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5704 li(scratch,
5705 ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5706 Lb(scratch, MemOperand(scratch));
5707 Branch(&skip_hook, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5708 }
5709 {
5710 // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
5711 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5712 Register receiver = temps.Acquire();
5713 LoadReceiver(receiver);
5714
5715 FrameScope frame(
5716 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5717 SmiTag(expected_parameter_count);
5718 Push(expected_parameter_count);
5719
5720 SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
5721 Push(actual_parameter_count);
5722
5723 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5724 Push(new_target);
5725 }
5726 Push(fun);
5727 Push(fun);
5728 Push(receiver);
5729 CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
5730 Pop(fun);
5731 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5732 Pop(new_target);
5733 }
5734
5735 Pop(actual_parameter_count);
5736 SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
5737
5738 Pop(expected_parameter_count);
5739 SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count);
5740 }
5741 bind(&skip_hook);
5742}
5743
5744void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
5745 Register expected_parameter_count,
5746 Register actual_parameter_count,
5747 InvokeType type) {
5748 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5749 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5750 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5751 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5752
5753 // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5754 CheckDebugHook(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5755 actual_parameter_count);
5756
5757 // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5758 if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5759 LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5760 }
5761
5762 Label done;
5763 InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, &done, type);
5764 // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5765 // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5766 // call sites.
5767 constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
5768 switch (type) {
5769 case InvokeType::kCall:
5770 CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
5771 break;
5772 case InvokeType::kJump:
5773 JumpJSFunction(function);
5774 break;
5775 }
5776
5777 // Continue here if InvokePrologue does handle the invocation due to
5778 // mismatched parameter counts.
5779 bind(&done);
5780}
5781
5782void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
5783 Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5784 InvokeType type) {
5785 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5786 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5787
5788 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5789 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5790 Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
5791 {
5792 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5793 Register temp_reg = temps.Acquire();
5794 LoadTaggedField(
5795 temp_reg,
5796 FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
5797 LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5798 // The argument count is stored as uint16_t
5799 Lhu(expected_parameter_count,
5800 FieldMemOperand(temp_reg,
5801 SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
5802 }
5803 InvokeFunctionCode(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5804 actual_parameter_count, type);
5805}
5806
5807void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function,
5808 Register expected_parameter_count,
5809 Register actual_parameter_count,
5810 InvokeType type) {
5811 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5812 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5813
5814 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5815 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5816
5817 // Get the function and setup the context.
5818 LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5819
5820 InvokeFunctionCode(a1, no_reg, expected_parameter_count,
5821 actual_parameter_count, type);
5822}

5837 SubWord(range, type_reg, Operand(lower_limit));
5838}

5841void MacroAssembler::WasmRvvEq(VRegister dst, VRegister lhs, VRegister rhs,
5842 VSew sew, Vlmul lmul) {

5846 vmv_vx(dst, zero_reg);
5847 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg, dst);
5848}
