5895#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5896void MacroAssembler::WasmRvvS128const(VRegister dst, const uint8_t imms[16]) {
5897 uint64_t vals[2];
5898 memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
5899 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5900 li(kScratchReg, vals[1]);
5901 vmv_sx(kSimd128ScratchReg, kScratchReg);
5902 vslideup_vi(dst, kSimd128ScratchReg, 1);
5903 li(kScratchReg, vals[0]);
5904 vmv_sx(dst, kScratchReg);
5905}
5906#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5907void MacroAssembler::WasmRvvS128const(VRegister dst, const uint8_t imms[16]) {
5908 uint32_t vals[4];
5909 memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
5910 VU.set(kScratchReg, VSew::E32, Vlmul::m1);
5911 li(kScratchReg, vals[3]);
5912 vmv_vx(kSimd128ScratchReg, kScratchReg);
5913 li(kScratchReg, vals[2]);
5914 vmv_sx(kSimd128ScratchReg, kScratchReg);
5915 li(kScratchReg, vals[1]);
5916 vmv_vx(dst, kScratchReg);
5917 li(kScratchReg, vals[0]);
5918 vmv_sx(dst, kScratchReg);
5919 vslideup_vi(dst, kSimd128ScratchReg, 2);
5920}
5921#endif
5922
5923void MacroAssembler::LoadLane(int ts, VRegister dst, uint8_t laneidx,
5924 MemOperand src, Trapper&& trapper) {
5925 DCHECK_NE(kScratchReg, src.rm());
5926 if (ts == 8) {
5927 Lbu(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5928 VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
5929 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5930 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5931 VU.set(kScratchReg, E8, m1);
5932 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5933 } else if (ts == 16) {
5934 Lhu(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5935 VU.set(kScratchReg, E16, m1);
5936 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5937 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5938 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5939 } else if (ts == 32) {
5940 Load32U(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5941 VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
5942 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5943 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5944 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5945 } else if (ts == 64) {
5946#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5947 LoadWord(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5948 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5949 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5950 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5951 vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
5952#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5953 LoadDouble(kScratchDoubleReg, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5954 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5955 li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
5956 vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
5957 vfmerge_vf(dst, kScratchDoubleReg, dst);
5958#endif
5959 } else {
5960 UNREACHABLE();
5961 }
5962}
5963
5964void MacroAssembler::StoreLane(int sz, VRegister src, uint8_t laneidx,
5965 MemOperand dst, Trapper&& trapper) {
5966 DCHECK_NE(kScratchReg, dst.rm());
5967 if (sz == 8) {
5968 VU.set(kScratchReg, E8, m1);
5969 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5970 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5971 Sb(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5972 } else if (sz == 16) {
5973 VU.set(kScratchReg, E16, m1);
5974 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5975 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5976 Sh(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5977 } else if (sz == 32) {
5978 VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
5979 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5980 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5981 Sw(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5982 } else {
5983 DCHECK_EQ(sz, 64);
5984 VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
5985 vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
5986#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5987 vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5988 StoreWord(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5989#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5990 vfmv_fs(kScratchDoubleReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
5991 StoreDouble(kScratchDoubleReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
5992#endif
5993 }
5994}
5995// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5996// Runtime calls.
5997#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5998void MacroAssembler::AddOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
5999 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6000 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6001 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6002 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6003 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6004 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6005 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6006 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6007 right_reg = scratch;
6008 } else {
6009 right_reg = right.rm();
6010 }
6011 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6012 overflow != scratch2);
6013 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6014 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6015 add(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6016 xor_(overflow, scratch2, left);
6017 xor_(scratch, scratch2, right_reg);
6018 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6019 Mv(dst, scratch2);
6020 } else {
6021 add(dst, left, right_reg);
6022 xor_(overflow, dst, left);
6023 xor_(scratch, dst, right_reg);
6024 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6025 }
6026}
6027
6028void MacroAssembler::SubOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
6029 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6030 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6031 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6032 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6033 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6034 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6035 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6036 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6037 right_reg = scratch;
6038 } else {
6039 right_reg = right.rm();
6040 }
6041
6042 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6043 overflow != scratch2);
6044 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6045
6046 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6047 sub(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6048 xor_(overflow, left, scratch2);
6049 xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
6050 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6051 Mv(dst, scratch2);
6052 } else {
6053 sub(dst, left, right_reg);
6054 xor_(overflow, left, dst);
6055 xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
6056 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6057 }
6058}
6059
6060void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
6061 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6062 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6063 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6064 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6065 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6066 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6067 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6068 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6069 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6070 right_reg = scratch;
6071 } else {
6072 right_reg = right.rm();
6073 }
6074
6075 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6076 overflow != scratch2);
6077 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6078 sext_w(overflow, left);
6079 sext_w(scratch2, right_reg);
6080
6081 mul(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
6082 sext_w(dst, overflow);
6083 xor_(overflow, overflow, dst);
6084}
6085
6086void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
6087 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6088 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6089 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6090 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6091 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6092 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6093 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6094 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6095 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6096 right_reg = scratch;
6097 } else {
6098 right_reg = right.rm();
6099 }
6100
6101 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6102 overflow != scratch2);
6103 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6104 // use this sequence of "mulh/mul" according to recommendation of ISA Spec 7.1
6105 // upper part
6106 mulh(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6107 // lower part
6108 mul(dst, left, right_reg);
6109 // expand the sign of the lower part to 64bit
6110 srai(overflow, dst, 63);
6111 // if the upper part is not eqaul to the expanded sign bit of the lower part,
6112 // overflow happens
6113 xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
6114}
6115
6116#elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
6117void MacroAssembler::AddOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
6118 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6119 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6120 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6121 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6122 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6123 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6124 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6125 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6126 right_reg = scratch;
6127 } else {
6128 right_reg = right.rm();
6129 }
6130 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6131 overflow != scratch2);
6132 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6133 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6134 add(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6135 xor_(overflow, scratch2, left);
6136 xor_(scratch, scratch2, right_reg);
6137 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6138 Mv(dst, scratch2);
6139 } else {
6140 add(dst, left, right_reg);
6141 xor_(overflow, dst, left);
6142 xor_(scratch, dst, right_reg);
6143 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6144 }
6145}
6146
6147void MacroAssembler::SubOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
6148 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6149 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6150 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6151 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6152 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6153 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6154 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6155 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6156 right_reg = scratch;
6157 } else {
6158 right_reg = right.rm();
6159 }
6160
6161 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6162 overflow != scratch2);
6163 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6164
6165 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6166 sub(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6167 xor_(overflow, left, scratch2);
6168 xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
6169 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6170 Mv(dst, scratch2);
6171 } else {
6172 sub(dst, left, right_reg);
6173 xor_(overflow, left, dst);
6174 xor_(scratch, left, right_reg);
6175 and_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6176 }
6177}
6178
6179void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
6180 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6181 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6182 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6183 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6184 Register right_reg = no_reg;
6185 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6186 Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6187 if (!right.is_reg()) {
6188 li(scratch, Operand(right));
6189 right_reg = scratch;
6190 } else {
6191 right_reg = right.rm();
6192 }
6193
6194 DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6195 overflow != scratch2);
6196 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6197 mulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
6198 mul(dst, left, right_reg);
6199 srai(scratch2, dst, 31);
6200 xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
6201}
6202#endif
6203
6204void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
6205 int num_arguments) {
6206 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6207 // All parameters are on the stack. a0 has the return value after call.
6208
6209 // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
6210 // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
6211 // expectation.
6212 CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
6213
6214 // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
6215 // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
6216 // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
6217 // smarter.
6218 PrepareCEntryArgs(num_arguments);
6219 PrepareCEntryFunction(ExternalReference::Create(f));
6220#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
6221 bool switch_to_central = options().is_wasm;
6222 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central));
6223#else
6224 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(1));
6225#endif
6226}
6227
6228void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
6229 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6230 const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
6231 DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
6232 if (function->nargs >= 0) {
6233 PrepareCEntryArgs(function->nargs);
6234 }
6235 JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
6236}
6237
6238void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
6239 bool builtin_exit_frame) {
6240 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6241 PrepareCEntryFunction(builtin);
6242 TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
6243}
6244
6245void MacroAssembler::LoadWeakValue(Register out, Register in,
6246 Label* target_if_cleared) {
6247 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6248 CompareTaggedAndBranch(target_if_cleared, eq, in,
6249 Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));
6250 And(out, in, Operand(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
6251}
6252
6253void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
6254 Register scratch1,
6255 Register scratch2) {
6256 DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
6257 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
6258 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6259 // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
6260 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t
6261 // dummy_stats_counter_ field.
6262 li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
6263 Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6264 Add32(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
6265 Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6266 }
6267}
6268
6269void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
6270 Register scratch1,
6271 Register scratch2) {
6272 DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
6273 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
6274 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6275 // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
6276 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t
6277 // dummy_stats_counter_ field.
6278 li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
6279 Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6280 Sub32(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
6281 Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6282 }
6283}

6285// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6286// Debugging.
6287
6288void MacroAssembler::Trap() { stop(); }
6289void MacroAssembler::DebugBreak() { stop(); }
6290
6291void MacroAssembler::Assert(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
6292 Operand rt) {
6293 if (v8_flags.debug_code) Check(cc, reason, rs, rt);
6294}
6295
6296void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
6297 Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
6298 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
6299
6300 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6301 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
6302 Label ok;
6303
6304 JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
6305
6306 GetObjectType(object, map_tmp, tmp);
6307
6308 Branch(&ok, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, tmp, Operand(LAST_NAME_TYPE));
6309
6310 Branch(&ok, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, tmp, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6311
6312 Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
6313
6314 Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
6315
6316 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6317
6318 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
6319
6320 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
6321
6322 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
6323
6324 Abort(abort_reason);
6325 bind(&ok);
6326}
6327
6328#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
6329
6330void MacroAssembler::AssertZeroExtended(Register int32_register) {
6331 if (!v8_flags.slow_debug_code) return;
6332 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6333 Assert(Condition::ule, AbortReason::k32BitValueInRegisterIsNotZeroExtended,
6334 int32_register, Operand(kMaxUInt32));
6335}
6336
6337#endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
6338
6339void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
6340 Operand rt) {
6341 Label L;
6342 BranchShort(&L, cc, rs, rt);
6343 Abort(reason);
6344 // Will not return here.
6345 bind(&L);
6346}
6347
6348void MacroAssembler::SbxCheck(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
6349 Operand rt) {
6350 Check(cc, reason, rs, rt);
6351}
6352
6353void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
6354 Label abort_start;
6355 bind(&abort_start);
6356 if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
6357 const char* msg = GetAbortReason(reason);
6358 RecordComment("Abort message: ");
6359 RecordComment(msg);
6360 }
6361
6362 // Avoid emitting call to builtin if requested.
6363 if (trap_on_abort()) {
6364 ebreak();
6365 return;
6366 }
6367
6368 if (should_abort_hard()) {
6369 // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
6370 FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
6371 PrepareCallCFunction(1, a0);
6372 li(a0, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
6373 li(a1, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
6374 // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
6375 // return anyway.
6376 Call(a1);
6377 return;
6378 }
6379
6380 Move(a0, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
6381
6382 {
6383 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
6384 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
6385 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
6386 if (root_array_available()) {
6387 // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
6388 // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
6389 // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
6390 // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
6391 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, t6);
6392 Call(t6);
6393 } else {
6394 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
6395 }
6396 }
6397 // Will not return here.
6398 if (is_trampoline_pool_blocked()) {
6399 // If the calling code cares about the exact number of
6400 // instructions generated, we insert padding here to keep the size
6401 // of the Abort macro constant.
6402 // Currently in debug mode with debug_code enabled the number of
6403 // generated instructions is 10, so we use this as a maximum value.
6404 static const int kExpectedAbortInstructions = 10;
6405 int abort_instructions = InstructionsGeneratedSince(&abort_start);
6406 DCHECK_LE(abort_instructions, kExpectedAbortInstructions);
6407 while (abort_instructions++ < kExpectedAbortInstructions) {
6408 nop();
6409 }
6410 }
6411}
6412
6413// Sets condition flags based on comparison, and returns type in type_reg.
6414void MacroAssembler::CompareObjectTypeAndJump(Register object, Register map,
6415 Register type_reg,
6416 InstanceType type, Condition cond,
6417 Label* target,
6418 Label::Distance distance) {
6419 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6420 LoadMap(map, object);
6421 // Borrowed from BaselineAssembler
6422 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6423 AssertNotSmi(map);
6424 Register temp_type_reg = type_reg;
6425 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6426 if (map == temp_type_reg) {
6427 // GetObjectType clobbers 2nd and 3rd args, can't be same registers as
6428 // first one
6429 temp_type_reg = temps.Acquire();
6430 }
6431 GetObjectType(map, temp_type_reg, temp_type_reg);
6432 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue, temp_type_reg, Operand(MAP_TYPE));
6433 }
6434 Lhu(type_reg, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
6435 Branch(target, cond, type_reg, Operand(type), distance);
6436}
6437
6438void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {
6439 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6440 LoadTaggedField(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
6441}
6442
6443void MacroAssembler::LoadCompressedMap(Register dst, Register object) {
6444 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6445 Lw(dst, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
6446}
6447
6448void MacroAssembler::LoadNativeContextSlot(Register dst, int index) {
6449 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6450 LoadMap(dst, cp);
6451 LoadTaggedField(
6452 dst, FieldMemOperand(
6453 dst, Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset));
6454 LoadTaggedField(dst, MemOperand(dst, Context::SlotOffset(index)));
6455}
6456
6457void MacroAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
6458 CodeKind min_opt_level,
6459 Register feedback_vector,
6460 FeedbackSlot slot,
6461 Label* on_result,
6462 Label::Distance distance) {
6463 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6464 Label fallthrough, clear_slot;
6465 LoadTaggedField(
6466 scratch_and_result,
6467 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6468 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6469 LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
6470
6471 // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
6472 {
6473 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
6474 LoadCodePointerField(
6475 scratch_and_result,
6476 FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
6477
6478 // marked for deoptimization?
6479 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6480 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6481 Load32U(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6482 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
6483
6484 if (min_opt_level == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
6485 Branch(&clear_slot, not_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
6486 Label::Distance::kNear);
6487
6488 // is code "turbofanned"?
6489 Load32U(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6490 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kIsTurbofannedBit));
6491 Branch(on_result, not_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg), distance);
6492
6493 Branch(&fallthrough);
6494 } else {
6495 DCHECK_EQ(min_opt_level, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
6496 Branch(on_result, equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg), distance);
6497 }
6498
6499 bind(&clear_slot);
6500 li(scratch_and_result, ClearedValue());
6501 StoreTaggedField(
6502 scratch_and_result,
6503 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6504 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6505 }
6506
6507 bind(&fallthrough);
6508 Move(scratch_and_result, zero_reg);
6509}
6510
6511void MacroAssembler::StubPrologue(StackFrame::Type type) {
6512 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6513 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6514 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6515 li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
6516 PushCommonFrame(scratch);
6517}
6518
6519void MacroAssembler::Prologue() { PushStandardFrame(a1); }
6520
6521void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
6522 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6523 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6524 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6525 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6526 Push(ra, fp);
6527 Move(fp, sp);
6528 if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
6529 li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
6530 Push(scratch);
6531 }
6532#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6533 if (type == StackFrame::WASM || type == StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP) {
6534 Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
6535 }
6536#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6537}
6538
6539void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
6540 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6541 addi(sp, fp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
6542 LoadWord(ra, MemOperand(fp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
6543 LoadWord(fp, MemOperand(fp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize));
6544}
6545
6546void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(Register scratch, int stack_space,
6547 StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
6548 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6549 DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
6550 frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
6551 frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
6552 frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
6553
6554 // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
6555 static_assert(2 * kSystemPointerSize ==
6556 ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
6557 static_assert(1 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
6558 static_assert(0 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
6559
6560 // This is how the stack will look:
6561 // fp + 2 (==kCallerSPDisplacement) - old stack's end
6562 // [fp + 1 (==kCallerPCOffset)] - saved old ra
6563 // [fp + 0 (==kCallerFPOffset)] - saved old fp
6564 // [fp - 1 StackFrame::EXIT Smi
6565 // [fp - 2 (==kSPOffset)] - sp of the called function
6566 // fp - (2 + stack_space + alignment) == sp == [fp - kSPOffset] - top of the
6567 // new stack (will contain saved ra)
6568
6569 using ER = ExternalReference;
6570
6571 // Save registers and reserve room for saved entry sp.
6572 addi(sp, sp,
6573 -2 * kSystemPointerSize - ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
6574 StoreWord(ra, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize));
6575 StoreWord(fp, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize));
6576
6577 li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
6578 StoreWord(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
6579 // Set up new frame pointer.
6580 addi(fp, sp, ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
6581
6582 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6583 StoreWord(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
6584 }
6585
6586 // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
6587 ER c_entry_fp_address =
6588 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
6589 StoreWord(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
6590 ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
6591 StoreWord(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
6592
6593 const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6594
6595 // Reserve place for the return address, stack space and an optional slot
6596 // (used by DirectCEntry to hold the return value if a struct is
6597 // returned) and align the frame preparing for calling the runtime function.
6598 DCHECK_GE(stack_space, 0);
6599 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand((stack_space + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
6600 if (frame_alignment > 0) {
6601 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6602 And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment)); // Align stack.
6603 }
6604
6605 // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
6606 // location.
6607 addi(scratch, sp, kSystemPointerSize);
6608 StoreWord(scratch, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
6609}
6610
6611void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register scratch) {
6612 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6613 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6614 using ER = ExternalReference;
6615 // Clear top frame.
6616 // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
6617 ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
6618 LoadWord(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
6619
6620 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6621 li(scratch, Operand(Context::kInvalidContext));
6622 StoreWord(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
6623 }
6624
6625 // Clear the top frame.
6626 ER c_entry_fp_address =
6627 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
6628 StoreWord(zero_reg, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
6629
6630 // Pop the arguments, restore registers, and return.
6631 Mv(sp, fp); // Respect ABI stack constraint.
6632 LoadWord(fp, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
6633 LoadWord(ra, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
6634
6635 addi(sp, sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
6636}
6637
6638int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
6639#if V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6640 // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
6641 // environment.
6642 // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one RISC-V
6643 // platform for another RISC-V platform with a different alignment.
6644 return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6645#else // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6646 // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
6647 // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
6648 // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
6649 // flag.
6650 return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
6651#endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6652}
6653
6654void MacroAssembler::AssertStackIsAligned() {
6655 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6656 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6657 const int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
6658 const int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
6659
6660 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
6661 Label alignment_as_expected;
6662 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6663 {
6664 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6665 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6666 andi(scratch, sp, frame_alignment_mask);
6667 BranchShort(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6668 }
6669 // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort re-entering here.
6670 ebreak();
6671 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
6672 }
6673 }
6674}
6675
6676void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
6677 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6678 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
6679 Lw(dst, MemOperand(src.rm(), SmiWordOffset(src.offset())));
6680 } else {
6681 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
6682 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
6683 Lw(dst, src);
6684 } else {
6685 LoadWord(dst, src);
6686 }
6687 SmiUntag(dst);
6688 }
6689}

6691void MacroAssembler::SmiToInt32(Register smi) {
6692 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6693 if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) {
6694 AssertSmi(smi);
6695 }
6696 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
6697 SmiUntag(smi);
6698}
6699
6700void MacroAssembler::SmiToInt32(Register dst, Register src) {
6701 if (dst != src) {
6702 Move(dst, src);
6703 }
6704 SmiToInt32(dst);
6705}

6707void MacroAssembler::JumpIfSmi(Register value, Label* smi_label,
6708 Label::Distance distance) {
6709 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6710 DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
6711 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6712 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6713 andi(scratch, value, kSmiTagMask);
6714 Branch(smi_label, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg), distance);
6715}
6716
6717void MacroAssembler::JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(
6718 Register code, Register scratch, Label* if_marked_for_deoptimization) {
6719 Load32U(scratch, FieldMemOperand(code, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6720 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
6721 Branch(if_marked_for_deoptimization, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6722}

6724Operand MacroAssembler::ClearedValue() const {
6725 return Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(i::ClearedValue(isolate()).ptr()));
6726}

6728void MacroAssembler::JumpIfNotSmi(Register value, Label* not_smi_label,
6729 Label::Distance distance) {
6730 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6731 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6732 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6733 DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
6734 andi(scratch, value, kSmiTagMask);
6735 Branch(not_smi_label, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg), distance);
6736}
6737
6738void MacroAssembler::JumpIfObjectType(Label* target, Condition cc,
6739 Register object,
6740 InstanceType instance_type,
6741 Register scratch) {
6742 DCHECK(cc == eq || cc == ne);
6743 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6744 if (scratch == no_reg) {
6745 scratch = temps.Acquire();
6746 }
6747 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
6748 if (std::optional<RootIndex> expected =
6749 InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(instance_type)) {
6750 Tagged_t ptr = ReadOnlyRootPtr(*expected);
6751 LoadCompressedMap(scratch, object);
6752 Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(ptr));
6753 return;
6754 }
6755 }
6756 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6757 Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(instance_type));
6758}
6759
6760void MacroAssembler::JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Register heap_object,
6761 Register scratch, Label* target,
6762 Label::Distance distance,
6763 Condition cc) {
6764 CHECK(cc == Condition::kUnsignedLessThan ||
6765 cc == Condition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual);
6766 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
6767#ifdef DEBUG
6768 Label ok;
6769 LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
6770 GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, scratch);
6771 Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
6772 Operand(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE - FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6773
6774 LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
6775 GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE,
6776 scratch);
6777 Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
6778 Operand(LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE -
6779 FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE));
6780
6781 Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidReceiver);
6782 bind(&ok);
6783#endif // DEBUG
6784
6785 // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
6786 // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
6787 // addresses.
6788 LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
6789 Branch(target, cc, scratch,
6790 Operand(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit));
6791 } else {
6792 static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
6793 GetObjectType(heap_object, scratch, scratch);
6794 Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6795 }
6796}

6798void MacroAssembler::AssertNotSmi(Register object, AbortReason reason) {
6799 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6800 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6801 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6802 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6803 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6804 andi(scratch, object, kSmiTagMask);
6805 Check(ne, reason, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6806 }
6807}

6809void MacroAssembler::AssertSmi(Register object, AbortReason reason) {
6810 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6811 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6812 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6813 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6814 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6815 andi(scratch, object, kSmiTagMask);
6816 Check(eq, reason, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6817 }
6818}
6819
6820void MacroAssembler::AssertConstructor(Register object) {
6821 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6822 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6823 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6824 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6825 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6826 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6827 SmiTst(object, scratch);
6828 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAConstructor, scratch,
6829 Operand(zero_reg));
6830
6831 LoadMap(scratch, object);
6832 Lbu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
6833 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
6834 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAConstructor, scratch,
6835 Operand(zero_reg));
6836 }
6837}
6838
6839void MacroAssembler::AssertFunction(Register object) {
6840 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6841 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6842 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6843 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6844 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6845 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6846 SmiTst(object, scratch);
6847 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction, scratch,
6848 Operand(zero_reg));
6849 push(object);
6850 LoadMap(object, object);
6851 Register range = scratch;
6852 GetInstanceTypeRange(object, object, FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, range);
6853 Check(Uless_equal, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFunction, range,
6854 Operand(LAST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE - FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));
6855 pop(object);
6856 }
6857}
6858
6859void MacroAssembler::AssertCallableFunction(Register object) {
6860 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
6861 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6862 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6863 AssertNotSmi(object, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction);
6864 push(object);
6865 LoadMap(object, object);
6866 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6867 Register range = temps.Acquire();
6868 GetInstanceTypeRange(object, object, FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, range);
6869 Check(Uless_equal, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotACallableFunction, range,
6870 Operand(LAST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE -
6871 FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));
6872 pop(object);
6873}
6874
6875void MacroAssembler::AssertBoundFunction(Register object) {
6876 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6877 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6878 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6879 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6880 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6881 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6882 SmiTst(object, scratch);
6883 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotABoundFunction, scratch,
6884 Operand(zero_reg));
6885 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6886 Check(eq, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotABoundFunction, scratch,
6887 Operand(JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE));
6888 }
6889}
6890
6891#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
6892void MacroAssembler::AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(
6893 Register object) {
6894#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
6895 if (!PointerCompressionIsEnabled()) return;
6896 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
6897 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6898 // We may not have any scratch registers so we preserve our input register.
6899 Push(object, zero_reg);
6900 Label ok;
6901 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6902 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6903 SmiTst(object, scratch);
6904 BranchShort(&ok, kEqual, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6905 // Clear the lower 32 bits.
6906 Srl64(object, object, Operand(32));
6907 Sll64(object, object, Operand(32));
6908 // Either the value is now equal to the right-shifted pointer compression
6909 // cage base or it's zero if we got a compressed pointer register as input.
6910 BranchShort(&ok, kEqual, object, Operand(zero_reg));
6911 Check(kEqual, AbortReason::kObjectNotTagged, object,
6912 Operand(kPtrComprCageBaseRegister));
6913 bind(&ok);
6914 Pop(object, zero_reg);
6915#endif
6916}
6917#endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
6918
6919void MacroAssembler::AssertGeneratorObject(Register object) {
6920 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
6921 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6922 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6923 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6924 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6925 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
6926 SmiTst(object, scratch);
6927 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAGeneratorObject, scratch,
6928 Operand(zero_reg));
6929
6930 LoadMap(scratch, object);
6931 GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE,
6932 scratch);
6933 Check(
6934 Uless_equal, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAGeneratorObject, scratch,
6935 Operand(LAST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE - FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE));
6936}
6937
6938void MacroAssembler::AssertUndefinedOrAllocationSite(Register object,
6939 Register scratch) {
6940 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6941 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6942 Label done_checking;
6943 AssertNotSmi(object);
6944 LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6945 BranchShort(&done_checking, eq, object, Operand(scratch));
6946 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6947 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedUndefinedOrCell, scratch,
6948 Operand(ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE));
6949 bind(&done_checking);
6950 }
6951}
6952
6953template <typename F_TYPE>
6954void MacroAssembler::FloatMinMaxHelper(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
6955 FPURegister src2, MaxMinKind kind) {
6956 DCHECK((std::is_same<F_TYPE, float>::value) ||
6957 (std::is_same<F_TYPE, double>::value));
6958
6959 if (src1 == src2 && dst != src1) {
6960 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6961 fmv_s(dst, src1);
6962 } else {
6963 fmv_d(dst, src1);
6964 }
6965 return;
6966 }
6967
6968 Label done, nan;
6969
6970 // For RISCV, fmin_s returns the other non-NaN operand as result if only one
6971 // operand is NaN; but for JS, if any operand is NaN, result is Nan. The
6972 // following handles the discrepency between handling of NaN between ISA and
6973 // JS semantics
6974 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6975 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6976 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6977 CompareIsNotNanF32(scratch, src1, src2);
6978 } else {
6979 CompareIsNotNanF64(scratch, src1, src2);
6980 }
6981 BranchFalseF(scratch, &nan);
6982
6983 if (kind == MaxMinKind::kMax) {
6984 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6985 fmax_s(dst, src1, src2);
6986 } else {
6987 fmax_d(dst, src1, src2);
6988 }
6989 } else {
6990 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
6991 fmin_s(dst, src1, src2);
6992 } else {
6993 fmin_d(dst, src1, src2);
6994 }
6995 }
6996 j(&done);
6997
6998 bind(&nan);
6999 // if any operand is NaN, return NaN (fadd returns NaN if any operand is NaN)
7000 if (std::is_same<float, F_TYPE>::value) {
7001 fadd_s(dst, src1, src2);
7002 } else {
7003 fadd_d(dst, src1, src2);
7004 }
7005
7006 bind(&done);
7007}
7008
7009void MacroAssembler::Float32Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7010 FPURegister src2) {
7011 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7012 FloatMinMaxHelper<float>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMax);
7013}
7014
7015void MacroAssembler::Float32Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7016 FPURegister src2) {
7017 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7018 FloatMinMaxHelper<float>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMin);
7019}
7020
7021void MacroAssembler::Float64Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7022 FPURegister src2) {
7023 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7024 FloatMinMaxHelper<double>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMax);
7025}
7026
7027void MacroAssembler::Float64Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7028 FPURegister src2) {
7029 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7030 FloatMinMaxHelper<double>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMin);
7031}
7032
7033int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedDWords(int num_gp_arguments,
7034 int num_fp_arguments) {
7035 int stack_passed_dwords = 0;
7036
7037 // Up to eight integer arguments are passed in registers a0..a7 and
7038 // up to eight floating point arguments are passed in registers fa0..fa7
7039 if (num_gp_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
7040 stack_passed_dwords += num_gp_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
7041 }
7042 if (num_fp_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
7043 stack_passed_dwords += num_fp_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
7044 }
7045 stack_passed_dwords += kCArgSlotCount;
7046 return stack_passed_dwords;
7047}
7048
7049void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
7050 int num_double_arguments,
7051 Register scratch) {
7052 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7053 int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
7054
7055 // Up to eight simple arguments in a0..a7, fa0..fa7.
7056 // Remaining arguments are pushed on the stack (arg slot calculation handled
7057 // by CalculateStackPassedDWords()).
7058 int stack_passed_arguments =
7059 CalculateStackPassedDWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
7060 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
7061 // Make stack end at alignment and make room for stack arguments and the
7062 // original value of sp.
7063 Mv(scratch, sp);
7064 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand((stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
7065 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
7066 And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment));
7067 StoreWord(scratch,
7068 MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7069 } else {
7070 SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7071 }
7072}
7073
7074void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
7075 Register scratch) {
7076 PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
7077}
7078
7079int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function,
7080 int num_reg_arguments,
7081 int num_double_arguments,
7082 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
7083 Label* return_location) {
7084 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
7085 li(t6, function);
7086 return CallCFunctionHelper(t6, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
7087 set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
7088}
7089
7090int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_reg_arguments,
7091 int num_double_arguments,
7092 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
7093 Label* return_location) {
7094 return CallCFunctionHelper(function, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
7095 set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
7096}
7097
7098int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function, int num_arguments,
7099 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
7100 Label* return_location) {
7101 return CallCFunction(function, num_arguments, 0, set_isolate_data_slots,
7102 return_location);
7103}
7104
7105int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_arguments,
7106 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
7107 Label* return_location) {
7108 return CallCFunction(function, num_arguments, 0, set_isolate_data_slots,
7109 return_location);
7110}
7111
7112int MacroAssembler::CallCFunctionHelper(
7113 Register function, int num_reg_arguments, int num_double_arguments,
7114 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots, Label* return_location) {
7115 DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
7116 DCHECK(has_frame());
7117 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7118 // Make sure that the stack is aligned before calling a C function unless
7119 // running in the simulator. The simulator has its own alignment check which
7120 // provides more information.
7121 // The argument stots are presumed to have been set up by
7122 // PrepareCallCFunction.
7123
7124#if V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
7125 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7126 int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
7127 int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
7128 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
7129 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
7130 Label alignment_as_expected;
7131 {
7132 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7133 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7134 And(scratch, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
7135 BranchShort(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7136 }
7137 // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort possibly
7138 // re-entering here.
7139 ebreak();
7140 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
7141 }
7142 }
7143#endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
7144
7145 // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
7146 // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
7147 // stays correct.
7148 Label get_pc;
7149 {
7150 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
7151 if (function != t6) {
7152 Mv(t6, function);
7153 function = t6;
7154 }
7155
7156 // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains
7157 // iterable, even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS
7158 // and C frames.
7159 // 't' registers are caller-saved so this is safe as a scratch register.
7160 Register pc_scratch = t1;
7161
7162 LoadAddress(pc_scratch, &get_pc);
7163 // See x64 code for reasoning about how to address the isolate data
7164 // fields.
7165 CHECK(root_array_available());
7166 StoreWord(pc_scratch,
7167 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
7168 StoreWord(fp,
7169 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
7170 }
7171 }
7172
7173 Call(function);
7174 int call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
7175 bind(&get_pc);
7176 if (return_location) bind(return_location);
7177
7178 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
7179 // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
7180 StoreWord(zero_reg,
7181 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
7182 }
7183
7184 // Remove frame bought in PrepareCallCFunction
7185 int stack_passed_arguments =
7186 CalculateStackPassedDWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
7187 if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
7188 LoadWord(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7189 } else {
7190 AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7191 }
7192
7193 return call_pc_offset;
7194}
7195
7196#undef BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK
7197
7198void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, int mask, Condition cc,
7199 Label* condition_met) {
7200 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7201 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7202 temps.Include(t6);
7203 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7204 And(scratch, object, Operand(~MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
7205 LoadWord(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()));
7206 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(mask));
7207 Branch(condition_met, cc, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7208}
7209
7210Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
7211 Register reg4, Register reg5,
7212 Register reg6) {
7213 RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
7214
7215 const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
7216 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
7217 int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
7218 Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
7219 if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
7220 return candidate;
7221 }
7222 UNREACHABLE();
7223}
7224
7225void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
7226 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7227 auto pc = -pc_offset();
7228 auipc(dst, 0);
7229 if (pc != 0) {
7230 SubWord(dst, dst, pc);
7231 }
7232}
7233
7234// Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
7235// jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
7236// to:
7237// 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
7238// the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
7239// 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
7240// 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
7241void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized() {
7242 int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
7243 LoadProtectedPointerField(
7244 kScratchReg, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
7245 Lw(kScratchReg, FieldMemOperand(kScratchReg, Code::kFlagsOffset));
7246 And(kScratchReg, kScratchReg,
7247 Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
7248 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, ne, kScratchReg,
7249 Operand(zero_reg));
7250}
7251
7252void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
7253 DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
7254 Label*) {
7255 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7256 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
7257 LoadWord(t6, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
7258 IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
7259 Call(t6);
7260 DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
7261 (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
7262 : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
7263}
7264
7265void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeInstructionStart(Register destination,
7266 Register code_object,
7267 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
7268 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7269#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7270 LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
7271 destination,
7272 FieldMemOperand(code_object, Code::kSelfIndirectPointerOffset), tag);
7273#else
7274 LoadWord(destination,
7275 FieldMemOperand(code_object, Code::kInstructionStartOffset));
7276#endif
7277}
7278
7279void MacroAssembler::LoadProtectedPointerField(Register destination,
7280 MemOperand field_operand) {
7281 DCHECK(root_array_available());
7282#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7283 DecompressProtected(destination, field_operand);
7284#else
7285 LoadTaggedField(destination, field_operand);
7286#endif
7287}
7288
7289void MacroAssembler::CallCodeObject(Register code_object,
7290 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
7291 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7292 LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_object, code_object, tag);
7293 Call(code_object);
7294}
7295
7296void MacroAssembler::JumpCodeObject(Register code_object, CodeEntrypointTag tag,
7297 JumpMode jump_mode) {
7298 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7299 DCHECK_EQ(JumpMode::kJump, jump_mode);
7300 LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_object, code_object, tag);
7301 Jump(code_object);
7302}
7303
7304void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
7305 uint16_t argument_count) {
7306 DCHECK_WITH_MSG(!V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL,
7307 "argument_count is only used with Leaptiering");
7308 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7309 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7310#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7311 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7312 Register dispatch_handle = t0;
7313 Register parameter_count = t1;
7314 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7315 Lw(dispatch_handle,
7316 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
7317 LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(code, parameter_count,
7318 dispatch_handle, scratch);
7319 Label match;
7320 Branch(&match, le, parameter_count, Immediate(argument_count));
7321 // If the parameter count doesn't match, we force a safe crash by setting the
7322 // code entrypoint to zero, causing a nullptr dereference during the call.
7323 mv(code, zero_reg);
7324 bind(&match);
7325 Call(code);
7326#elif V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7327 // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
7328 // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
7329 // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
7330 LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
7331 code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
7332 kJSEntrypointTag);
7333 Call(code);
7334#else
7335 LoadTaggedField(code,
7336 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
7337 CallCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag);
7338#endif
7339}
7340
7341#if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7342void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
7343 uint16_t argument_count) {
7344 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7345 Register scratch = s1;
7346 li(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister,
7347 Operand(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
7348 // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
7349 // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the li above (thus keeping the
7350 // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
7351 // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
7352 // invalidated by a compaction).
7353 // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
7354 static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
7355 LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
7356 CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
7357 IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
7358 dispatch_handle));
7359 Call(code);
7360}
7361#endif
7362
7363void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
7364 JumpMode jump_mode) {
7365 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7366 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7367#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7368 LoadCodeEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
7369 code,
7370 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
7371 DCHECK_EQ(jump_mode, JumpMode::kJump);
7372 DCHECK_NE(code, t6);
7373 mv(t6, code);
7374 Jump(t6);
7375#elif V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7376 // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
7377 // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
7378 // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
7379 LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
7380 code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
7381 kJSEntrypointTag);
7382 DCHECK_EQ(jump_mode, JumpMode::kJump);
7383 // We jump through x17 here because for Branch Identification (BTI) we use
7384 // "Call" (`bti c`) rather than "Jump" (`bti j`) landing pads for tail-called
7385 // code. See TailCallBuiltin for more information.
7386 DCHECK_NE(code, t6);
7387 mv(t6, code);
7388 Jump(t6);
7389#else
7390 LoadTaggedField(code,
7391 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
7392 JumpCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
7393#endif
7394}
7395
7396#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7397void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target,
7398 uint64_t signature_hash) {
7399 static_assert(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
7400 ExternalReference global_jump_table =
7401 ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
7402 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7403 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7404 li(scratch, global_jump_table);
7405
7406#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7407 static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 16);
7408 Alsl_d(target, target, scratch, 4);
7409 LoadWord(
7410 scratch,
7411 MemOperand(target, wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kOffsetOfSignatureHash));
7412 bool has_second_tmp = temps.hasAvailable();
7413 Register signature_hash_register = has_second_tmp ? temps.Acquire() : target;
7414 if (!has_second_tmp) {
7415 Push(signature_hash_register);
7416 }
7417 li(signature_hash_register, Operand(signature_hash));
7418 SbxCheck(Condition::kEqual, AbortReason::kWasmSignatureMismatch, scratch,
7419 Operand(signature_hash_register));
7420 if (!has_second_tmp) {
7421 Pop(signature_hash_register);
7422 }
7423#else
7424 static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == kSystemPointerSize);
7425 CalcScaledAddress(target, scratch, target, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
7426#endif
7427 LoadWord(target, MemOperand(target, 0));
7428}
7429
7430void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
7431 uint64_t signature_hash,
7432 CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
7433 ResolveWasmCodePointer(target, signature_hash);
7434 if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
7435 Jump(target);
7436 } else {
7437 Call(target);
7438 }
7439}
7440
7441void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointerNoSignatureCheck(Register target) {
7442 ExternalReference global_jump_table =
7443 ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
7444 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7445 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7446 li(scratch, global_jump_table);
7447 constexpr unsigned int kEntrySizeLog2 =
7448 std::bit_width(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry)) - 1;
7449 CalcScaledAddress(target, scratch, target, kEntrySizeLog2);
7450 LoadWord(target, MemOperand(target));
7451 Call(target);
7452}
7453
7454void MacroAssembler::LoadWasmCodePointer(Register dst, MemOperand src) {
7455 static_assert(sizeof(WasmCodePointer) == 4);
7456 Lw(dst, src);
7457}
7458#endif
7459
7460#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7461void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(Register destination,
7462 Register dispatch_handle,
7463 Register scratch) {
7464 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
7465 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7466 li(scratch, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
7467 srli(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
7468 slli(index, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7469 AddWord(scratch, scratch, index);
7470 Ld(destination, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
7471}
7472
7473void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
7474 Register destination, JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle, Register scratch) {
7475 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
7476 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7477 li(scratch, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
7478 // WARNING: This offset calculation is only safe if we have already stored a
7479 // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle, e.g. in CallJSDispatchEntry, (thus
7480 // keeping the dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not
7481 // compatible (thus meaning that the offset calculation is not invalidated by
7482 // a compaction).
7483 // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
7484 static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
7485 int offset = JSDispatchTable::OffsetOfEntry(dispatch_handle) +
7486 JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset;
7487 Ld(destination, MemOperand(scratch, offset));
7488}
7489
7490void MacroAssembler::LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
7491 Register destination, Register dispatch_handle, Register scratch) {
7492 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
7493 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7494 Register index = destination;
7495 li(scratch, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
7496 srli(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
7497 slli(index, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7498 AddWord(scratch, scratch, index);
7499 static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
7500 Lh(destination, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
7501}
7502
7503void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
7504 Register entrypoint, Register parameter_count, Register dispatch_handle,
7505 Register scratch) {
7506 DCHECK(!AreAliased(entrypoint, parameter_count, scratch));
7507 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7508 Register index = parameter_count;
7509 li(scratch, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
7510 srli(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
7511 slli(index, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7512 AddWord(scratch, scratch, index);
7513
7514 Ld(entrypoint, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
7515 static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
7516 Lh(parameter_count, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
7517}
7518#endif

7520#if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
7521void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedField(const Register& destination,
7522 const MemOperand& field_operand,
7523 Trapper&& trapper) {
7524 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
7525 DecompressTagged(destination, field_operand,
7526 std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7527 } else {
7528 Ld(destination, field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7529 }
7530}
7531
7532void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedFieldWithoutDecompressing(
7533 const Register& destination, const MemOperand& field_operand) {
7534 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
7535 Lw(destination, field_operand);
7536 } else {
7537 Ld(destination, field_operand);
7538 }
7539}
7540
7541void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedSignedField(const Register& destination,
7542 const MemOperand& field_operand) {
7543 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
7544 DecompressTaggedSigned(destination, field_operand);
7545 } else {
7546 Ld(destination, field_operand);
7547 }
7548}
7549
7550void MacroAssembler::SmiUntagField(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
7551 SmiUntag(dst, src);
7552}
7553
7554void MacroAssembler::StoreTaggedField(const Register& value,
7555 const MemOperand& dst_field_operand,
7556 Trapper&& trapper) {
7557 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
7558 Sw(value, dst_field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7559 } else {
7560 Sd(value, dst_field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7561 }
7562}
7563
7564void MacroAssembler::AtomicStoreTaggedField(Register src,
7565 const MemOperand& dst) {
7566 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7567 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7568 AddWord(scratch, dst.rm(), dst.offset());
7569 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
7570 amoswap_w(true, true, zero_reg, src, scratch);
7571 } else {
7572 amoswap_d(true, true, zero_reg, src, scratch);
7573 }
7574}
7575
7576void MacroAssembler::DecompressTaggedSigned(const Register& destination,
7577 const MemOperand& field_operand) {
7578 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7579 Lwu(destination, field_operand);
7580 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
7581 // Corrupt the top 32 bits. Made up of 16 fixed bits and 16 pc offset bits.
7582 AddWord(destination, destination,
7583 Operand(((kDebugZapValue << 16) | (pc_offset() & 0xffff)) << 32));
7584 }
7585}
7586
7587void MacroAssembler::DecompressTagged(const Register& destination,
7588 const MemOperand& field_operand,
7589 Trapper&& trapper) {
7590 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7591 Lwu(destination, field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7592 AddWord(destination, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, destination);
7593}
7594
7595void MacroAssembler::DecompressTagged(const Register& destination,
7596 const Register& source) {
7597 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7598 And(destination, source, Operand(0xFFFFFFFF));
7599 AddWord(destination, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, Operand(destination));
7600}
7601
7602void MacroAssembler::DecompressTagged(Register dst, Tagged_t immediate) {
7603 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7604 AddWord(dst, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(immediate));
7605}
7606
7607void MacroAssembler::DecompressProtected(const Register& destination,
7608 const MemOperand& field_operand,
7609 Trapper&& trapper) {
7610#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7611 CHECK(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
7612 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7613 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7614 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7615 Lw(destination, field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7616 LoadWord(scratch,
7617 MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::trusted_cage_base_offset()));
7618 Or(destination, destination, scratch);
7619#else
7620 UNREACHABLE();
7621#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7622}
7623
7624void MacroAssembler::AtomicDecompressTaggedSigned(Register dst,
7625 const MemOperand& src) {
7626 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7627 Lwu(dst, src);
7628 sync();
7629 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
7630 // Corrupt the top 32 bits. Made up of 16 fixed bits and 16 pc offset bits.
7631 AddWord(dst, dst,
7632 Operand(((kDebugZapValue << 16) | (pc_offset() & 0xffff)) << 32));
7633 }
7634}
7635
7636void MacroAssembler::AtomicDecompressTagged(Register dst,
7637 const MemOperand& src) {
7638 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7639 Lwu(dst, src);
7640 sync();
7641 AddWord(dst, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, dst);
7642}

7644#endif
7645void MacroAssembler::DropArguments(Register count) {
7646 CalcScaledAddress(sp, sp, count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
7647}
7648
7649void MacroAssembler::DropArgumentsAndPushNewReceiver(Register argc,
7650 Register receiver) {
7651 DCHECK(!AreAliased(argc, receiver));
7652 DropArguments(argc);
7653 push(receiver);
7654}
7655
7656// Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
7657// from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
7658// and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
7659// (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
7660// (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
7661// allocated for the fast call).
7662void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
7663 Register function_address,
7664 ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
7665 int slots_to_drop_on_return,
7666 MemOperand* argc_operand,
7667 MemOperand return_value_operand) {
7668 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
7669 using ER = ExternalReference;
7670
7671 Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
7672 MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7673 ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
7674 MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7675 ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
7676 MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7677 ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
7678
7679 Register return_value = a0;
7680 Register scratch = a4;
7681 Register scratch2 = a5;
7682
7683 // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
7684 // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
7685 // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
7686 Register prev_next_address_reg = kScratchReg;
7687 Register prev_limit_reg = s1;
7688 Register prev_level_reg = s2;
7689
7690 // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
7691 // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
7692 // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
7693 // call).
7694 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
7695 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7696 // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
7697 // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
7698 // fine).
7699 DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
7700 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7701 DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
7702 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7703 {
7704 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
7705 "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
7706 __ LoadWord(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
7707 __ LoadWord(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
7708 __ Lw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
7709 __ Add32(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
7710 __ Sw(scratch, level_mem_op);
7711 }
7712
7713 Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
7714 if (with_profiling) {
7715 __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
7716 __ Lb(scratch,
7717 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
7718 __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
7719 Operand(zero_reg));
7720#ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
7721 __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
7722 __ li(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
7723 __ Lw(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
7724 __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
7725 Operand(zero_reg));
7726#endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
7727 }
7728
7729 __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
7730 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
7731 __ bind(&done_api_call);
7732
7733 Label propagate_exception;
7734 Label delete_allocated_handles;
7735 Label leave_exit_frame;
7736
7737 __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
7738 __ LoadWord(return_value, return_value_operand);
7739
7740 {
7741 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
7742 masm,
7743 "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
7744 "Restore previous handle scope.");
7745 __ StoreWord(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
7746 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7747 __ Lw(scratch, level_mem_op);
7748 __ Sub32(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
7749 __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall, scratch,
7750 Operand(prev_level_reg));
7751 }
7752 __ Sw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
7753 __ LoadWord(scratch, limit_mem_op);
7754 __ Branch(&delete_allocated_handles, ne, prev_limit_reg, Operand(scratch));
7755 }
7756 __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
7757 __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
7758
7759 Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
7760 if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
7761 // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
7762 __ LoadWord(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
7763 }
7764
7765 __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
7766
7767 {
7768 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
7769 "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
7770 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
7771 __ LoadWord(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7772 ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
7773 __ Branch(&propagate_exception, ne, scratch, Operand(scratch2));
7774 }
7775
7776 __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
7777 AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
7778
7779 if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
7780 DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
7781 __ AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
7782 } else {
7783 // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
7784 if (slots_to_drop_on_return != 0) {
7785 __ AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
7786 }
7787 __ CalcScaledAddress(sp, sp, argc_reg, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
7788 }
7789
7790 __ Ret();
7791
7792 if (with_profiling) {
7793 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
7794 __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
7795 // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
7796 if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
7797 MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7798 IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
7799 __ StoreWord(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
7800 }
7801 __ li(scratch, thunk_ref);
7802 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
7803 __ Branch(&done_api_call);
7804 }
7805
7806 __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
7807 __ bind(&propagate_exception);
7808 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
7809
7810 {
7811 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
7812 masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
7813 __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
7814 __ StoreWord(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
7815 // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
7816 Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
7817 __ Move(saved_result, a0);
7818 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, prev_level_reg);
7819 __ li(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address(isolate));
7820 __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
7821 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], saved_result);
7822 __ Branch(&leave_exit_frame);
7823 }
7824}
7825
7826void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
7827 Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
7828 Label done;
7829 // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
7830 LoadTaggedField(dst,
7831 FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
7832 LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
7833
7834 // Check if feedback vector is valid.
7835 LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
7836 Lhu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
7837 Branch(&done, eq, scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
7838
7839 // Not valid, load undefined.
7840 LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
7841 Branch(fbv_undef);
7842
7843 bind(&done);
7844}
7845
7846#undef __
7847} // namespace internal
7848} // namespace v8
